title: baked apple
directions: Bring sugar, water, cinnamon and butter to a boil.
Peel and core apples.
Pour sugar and cinnamon mixture in center.
Dot with butter.
Wrap each apple in pie crust dough.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes.
Pour remainder of mixture over and around apples during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: granny's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt; stir to dissolve.
Cool and combine with yeast.
Stir in eggs.
Gradually add 4 cups flour, beating well.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Work in remaining 2 to 4 cups flour to make a very soft dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. May be kept in refrigerator as long as a week; use as needed. Form into rolls; brush with melted margarine.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 45 minutes or until light.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until browned.

title: cubed steak - tender every time
directions: Roll steak in flour; place in oil and fry on high until brown on one side.
Turn steak, reduce heat to simmer.
Add water, cover and let simmer 20 to 30 minutes, depending on thickness of steak. Serve with a generous portion of love.
It makes the heart tender every time.

title: party delight
directions: Place cream cheese in medium bowl.
Gradually mix in sour cream.
Add flaked crab.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Put shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Makes 4 cups.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop the first 3 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients.
Place in a shallow dish and cover with 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese and 1 cup grated Muenster cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or Triskets crackers.

title: old-fashioned pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, peppers and celery.
Mix with remaining ingredients and boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: chocolate pie(this is easy and great!)
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla.
Mix with the first mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until straw comes out clean.

title: mimi's meat balls
directions: Mix all except soup.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place in lightly greased skillet.
Brown well on all sides.
Remove excess drippings.
Pour undiluted mushroom soup over all.
Simmer until tender and well done.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mixes, 1 cup of the milk and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer on high speed 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pudding mixes; beat on low speed.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: squash and onions
directions: Shred squash and onions in a frying pan.
Add pepper and salt. Put oil or bacon grease and cornmeal in pan.
Cover and stew until almost done.
Remove lid to finish until slightly browned.

title: peanut butter potato candy
directions: Boil the potato until well done.
Peel the potato while it is still hot and mash it rapidly, adding the powdered sugar.
Stir thoroughly each time sugar is added.
Continue to add sugar until the mixture is the consistency of biscuit dough.
Spread on wax paper.
Roll with rolling pin.
Spread on peanut butter to desired thickness.
Roll and leave in wax paper until chilled.
Slice in pinwheels and serve.

title: cocktail cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese, butter and paste until fluffy.
Add other ingredients.
Chill so you can mold.
Roll in nuts.
Make a day before serving.

title: juicy pineapple cake
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Take about 2 handfuls or so of brown sugar and spread around on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and prick all over with meat fork and pour sauce all over cake.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers.
Prepare pudding mix.
Let stand 5 minutes, then fold in the Cool Whip. Spread half the mixture over the graham crackers, then add another layer of graham crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture and crackers.
Spread pie filling on top of the last crackers.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.

title: bavarian festival cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts and butter; mix thoroughly and press into bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, cheese, oregano, pepper and salt; set aside.
Lightly saute garlic in 2 tablespoons butter; stir in remaining butter.
Dip chicken in garlic butter, roll each piece in breadcrumbs mixture and pour on remaining garlic butter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, bread, chicken, egg and spices; set aside.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, melt butter in microwave.
Pour 1/2 of butter in a cup; set aside.
Pour soup mixture into casserole dish, containing 1/2 of butter.
Crush crackers into fine crumbs. Add to reserved butter.
Mix and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Cool.
Blend in sugar, peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemon rice
directions: Combine rice, margarine, garlic, lemon peel, pepper and broth in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; stir once or twice.
Lower heat to simmer; cover with tight fitting lid.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour a little oil in bottom of baking dish.
Add garlic salt and pepper.
Place chicken in dish.
Dab with butter, then add 1 or 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and dabs of sour cream.
Last, add can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a soft boil stage.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until creamy and pour into pan.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: dip dogs
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cornmeal.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk and mix well.
Dip hot dogs in mixture.
Cook in deep fat until brown.

title: zucchini caponata
directions: Heat oil in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onions, celery and peppers.
Cook and stir 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Reduce heat to medium.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are softened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
Serve pita bread.

title: snowballs
directions: Soften butter and add sugar and mix well.
Add salt, flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and diced onion.
Drain meat mixture and return to pan.
Stir in mushroom soup, Ro-Tel, and beans.

Layer half of the tortillas evenly into 2 lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dishes. Top each with 1/4 of meat mixture and 1/4 cheese. Repeat layers with remaining tortillas, meat mixture, and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: deviled chicken wings
directions: Stir to moisten rice, then mix in the above ingredients; cover and simmer slowly 25-30 minutes.
Stir occasionally adding water as needed.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at
a
time.
Add extract.
Add flour, pecans, raisins, baking
powder and salt. Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours in greased Bundt pan.

title: fay's make ahead cookie mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine salt, butter and baking powder using an electric mixer to blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Do not scoop or sift flour. Add flour into butter mixture. Blend until mixture is like crumbs. Store tightly covered in refrigerator. Keeps up to 4 weeks. Makes 8 cups of mix.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in large greased rectangular dish. Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed potato chips mixed with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 2/3 cup toasted almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and form into balls of desired size.
Cook until brown.
Place into dish and cover with brown gravy.
Garnish with spaghetti.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Butter a 11 x 16-inch baking dish and sprinkle the rice on the bottom.
Lay the
chicken
pieces, skin side up, on the rice.
Mix soup, water
and
sherry;
pour
over
the chicken. Sprinkle the onion soup
mix
over
all.
Cover
tightly
with aluminum foil, making sure edges
are
sealed.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Do not peek or rice will burn.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and chicken into about 1-inch cubes.
Add garlic and oil into hot skillet; cook until chicken is done.
Remove from skillet.
Reheat pan and add wine so that it picks up flavors from skillet.
Slowly add cream, scallions, cayenne pepper, oregano and peas.
Mix cornstarch with about 4 ounces water.
Add a little at a time until you get a creamy sauce.
Add chicken and bacon mixture; heat.
Add black pepper to taste.
Serve over pasta.
Shrimp may be substituted for chicken.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Put butter in skillet.
Add rice and brown.
Add water and soup mix.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: holiday chicken and crab
directions: Grease bottom of large casserole dish and place layer of artichoke hearts; cover layer with mushrooms, finally topping with chicken & crab.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
While still hot, toss with Italian dressing; let stand 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jerrie's dressing
directions: Saut onion, celery and bell pepper in a stick of butter. Prepare the corn kits. Follow corn kit directions. Mix in corn kits and 1 quart of chicken broth. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Don't overcook.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine with eggs, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and soup.
Place in greased casserole and top with the Ritz crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Combine all sugars and spices.
Add butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Add ice cream and stir until blended.
Put in container and freeze.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Pat ground beef in bottom of greased pan.
Spread soup over meat and cover with cheese.
Top with tater tots.
Bake covered for 45 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes more.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ingredients by layers in order listed.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then cut into small squares.

title: artichokes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook artichokes according to package directions; drain.
Combine Parmesan cheese, dry bread crumbs and paprika; stir in the 1 teaspoon softened margarine or butter.
Set aside.

title: chicken and shrimp scampi
directions: Rub chicken well with salt and pepper.
In large skillet in hot butter, saute chicken until golden.
Add onions, garlic, parsley, wine, tomato sauce and basil.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Push chicken to one side of skillet.
Turn up heat so tomato mixture boils.
Add shrimp. Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes or until just pink.
Skim off any fat. Makes 6 servings.

title: reeses candy
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cracker crumbs and peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Melt chips; spread over mixture in pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares.
Note: Might want to score squares in chocolate before chilling.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on platter. Layer with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese. Top with black olives, if desired.
Place taco chips around platter.

title: american chop suey
directions: Fry pork, celery and onions together until brown.
Add tomatoes and cheese and simmer until thick.
Place cooked drained noodles in buttered baking dish.
Add meat mixture.
Season and brown in a 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding shrimp last.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: see's fudge
directions: In double boiler melt butter and chocolate.
Stir to blend. Blend in powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs; stir until well blended.
If desired stir in nuts and/or marshmallows.
Pour into 8 inch square pan.
Cut into squares when set.

title: cheddar cheese ring
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Lightly grease (Pam or other spray product) a 5 or 6-cup round mold and place mixture into mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Place jelly or preserves in center of the mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: shredded beef barbecue
directions: Put beef, onion and celery into pot; add water to cover and cook until tender.
Cook and shred.
Refrigerate broth until fat rises to top.
Remove fat; add 3 cups of broth to other ingredients.
Simmer mixture, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours over low heat with the meat.

title: leftover green beans
directions: Rinse green beans very well.
Put some butter in pan, then add chopped onion.
Let let 3 to 5 minutes, then pour beans in and let cook 5 minutes more.
Put vinegar in and let simmer slow for 3 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: *This can be adjusted based on personal taste.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Stir all dry ingredients.
Make wells.
Before mixing dry ingredients, shortening, vinegar and vanilla, pour hot coffee over and mix.
Add 5 eggs last.
Use 1/4 of recipe for 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix as directed on pan and bake in 9 x 13 inch pan until done. Let cool before adding toppings.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in crusts and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Pink lemonade or limeade may be used instead of lemonade.

title: low calorie angel cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients according to package directions. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet covered with foil or sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove cookies from sheet while still warm.
Makes 36 cookies.
One cookie contains 89 calories (27 calories from fat).

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes as small as desired; slice eggs.
Put in casserole, add celery and onions.
Cook bacon slowly, until lightly brown or crisp.
Add bacon to potatoes.

title: mother's chocolate frosting
directions: Mix ingredients well; boil for 1 minute or until thick. Remove and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: kentucky biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix quickly to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead a few times to make a soft dough (don't overknead or biscuits will turn hard and dry).
Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With knife, cut dough into 12 even portions.
Do not separate.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 15 minutes.
Dust with flour, if desired, when biscuits come out of oven.
Serve piping hot with butter, jam and/or honey.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook spaghetti, drain, rinse with cold water and toss with a small amount of vegetable oil.
Cook zucchini and green beans in a little water until just tender but still crisp and bright in color.
Rinse in cold water; drain and add to spaghetti along with onions, olives, tomatoes, salt and cheese.
Beat together last 5 ingredients until well blended. Toss lightly with spaghetti mixture.
Refrigerate overnight in a sealed 2-quart container.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix fruit. Add Eagle Brand milk. Fold in whipped topping and serve.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Boil together the sugar, syrup and cream until forms a soft ball.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered dish or pan; cut into squares.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with sour cream until smooth and creamy (1/2 package dry taco seasoning may also be added). Refrigerate until firm in 9 or 10-inch pan.
Spread taco sauce over cheese and sour cream mixture.
Top with green chilies, lettuce, tomato and shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix and boil butter, cocoa and cola; pour over flour and sugar.
Add soda, vanilla, eggs, buttermilk and marshmallows.
Bake in greased sheet pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat peanut butter until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla to the flour, salt and chocolate chips. Bake until done, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus spears into small pieces.
Place layer of asparagus in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place layer of hard-boiled eggs and cover with sauce or soup.
Repeat, making 2 or 3 layers.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook sausage, stirring to crumble; drain. Sprinkle sausage over croutons. Combine eggs, milk, soup, mushrooms and mustard. Mix well. Pour over sausage. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix bread, eggs and onion.
Put in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, mix celery, crab meat and mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pork chops o'brien(ready to bake in 15 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Drain.
Sprinkle chops with seasoning; set aside.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 of onions.
Spray 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Spoon mixture into dish.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chops are done.
Top chops with rest of cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more until brown.

title: potato almond balls
directions: Add egg to mashed potatoes before shaping and coating.
Heat melted butter or oleo.
Mashed potatoes formed into balls and rolled in toasted almonds are a real treat.
Make balls about 1 1/2-inches in circumference.

title: pape's potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes until soft.
Place on broiling rack and put butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 15 minutes until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple and oranges.
Add 2 cups juice to the 2 boxes of pudding.
Mix and cook until thick and it bubbles.
Cool, then add all the fruit.
Mix well.
Top with cherries.
Chill.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and water until tender on medium heat.
Add sugar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Mix in pie filling. Cook 6 to 8 minutes more.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Put in containers and freeze.
Keep refrigerated after thawing.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate and layer remaining ingredients in order shown above.
Serve with crackers.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cook carrots in 1/2 cup water; boil for 5 minutes.
Combine with cauliflower, broccoli, green peppers and mushrooms.
Combine mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Gradually add oil; stir briskly to blend.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat.
Chill thoroughly.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg, and add alternately with water.
Mix in can of soup with nuts and raisins.
Bake 45 minutes or 1 hour at 350°.
Use your own favorite caramel icing or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray coating.
In a bowl, stir together flour, 2 tablespoons of the sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center.
In small bowl combine egg, orange juice and oil and add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until moist; it will be lumpy.
Toss cranberries with 2 tablespoons sugar and stir into mixture.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 18 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from tins.
Makes 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 150 servings.

title: mexican special
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning.
Spread on large tray.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream and spread on top of bean mixture. Layer remaining ingredients with cheese on top.
Pour picante sauce over top.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: jello salad
directions: Put the sugar and pineapple juice on stove and let it come to a boil.
Add 1 package lemon Jell-O and cream cheese.
Mix and let cool until it starts to congeal.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Place in the refrigerator until it congeals.

title: earth apple soup(swiss potato soup)
directions: Dice and cook potatoes and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer until very tender, then mash.

title: aunt betty's spare ribs
directions: Pour all the above (after mixing together) over about 3 lbs. spare ribs and marinate about 4 hours.
Bake spare ribs with marinade about 2 hours at 325 degrees, basting occasionally.

title: cinnamon sugared nuts
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, salt and milk in saucepan. Stir while cooking to soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts, stirring until creamy.
Turn out quickly onto waxed paper and separate.

title: sour cream sugared pecans
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, mix sour cream, sugar and salt. Heat to 225° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir rapidly until mixture has coated nuts and sugared.
Spread on tray, separate nuts and cool. Store in tightly covered container.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Shake chicken in bag with flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Reserve 2 tablespoons of flour.
Brown chicken in butter.
Pour pan fat into measuring cup.
Return 3 tablespoons to skillet. Saute onion in fat about 10 minutes.
Add paprika, remaining 1/2 teaspoon of salt and chicken broth; bring to boil.
Lower heat. Return chicken.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes or until tender. Remove chicken.
Stir in light cream.
Make paste of reserved 2 tablespoons flour and sour cream.
Stir slowly into skillet. Cook, stirring constantly over low heat until thickened.
Do not boil.
Return chicken.
Serve over dumplings.

title: coconut-orange cake
directions: Combine
cake
mix, milk, egg whites and orange concentrate. Beat
minutes
at
medium
speed of electric mixer. Fold in the 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch
layer pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes; cool. Frost and fill with Fluffy White Frosting.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Combine all ingredients. Place in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until liquid is absorbed.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix in medium bowl milk, egg and sugar until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Heat in a heavy skillet or griddle over medium-high heat.
Grease lightly.
Using about 1/4 cup batter for each pancake, pour batter into skillet in shape of heart and cook until bubbles appear on surface and edges are dry.

title: chicken `65'
directions: Mix chicken with the next 8 ingredients.
Marinate for 3 hours.
Then deep-fry the chicken pieces.
Reserve the marinade.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix together last 5 ingredients.
Dice bacon and fry.
Leave 2 tablespoons drippings.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Add all beans, bacon bits and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or simmer on stove if desired.

title: sauce for eggplant parmesan
directions: Saute onion in olive oil with garlic.
Add tomatoes and sugar and cook 25 minutes.
Turn off and add sugar and spices.

title: lemon snow bars
directions: Stir together flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Put mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: french strawberry pudding
directions: Crumble wafers into fine crumbs.
Put half the crumbs in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: rum glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in preheated 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender.
Let cool.
Peel and cut diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange potatoes and apples in buttered 14-inch gratin dish and sprinkle the mixture with chestnuts.
In stainless steel or enameled saucepan, combine the butter, brown sugar, honey, rum, cinnamon, ginger and mace; cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, until the brown sugar is dissolved.

Spoon the syrup over the potatoes, apples and chestnuts mixture and bake in hot 400° oven, basting occasionally, for approximately 30 minutes, or until apples are tender and potatoes are heated through.
Put dish under broiler and brown lightly.
Serves 8.

title: chicken simplicity
directions: Sprinkle
dry
onion
soup
mix
and uncooked rice over bottom of
baking dish.
Place chicken on rice.
Combine soup and water.
Pour
over
the chicken and rice.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika on.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Do not open while baking.

title: green salad
directions: Simmer meat and beans 10 minutes until meat is a gray color. Cool mixture and add tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Tear lettuce in bite size pieces.
Toss with meat mixture and chill for 1 hour. When ready to serve, toss with salad dressing and crumble Doritos on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend milk, eggs and Bisquick together in blender, then stir in ham, broccoli and cheese (may add chopped onions if desired). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: no peek oven stew
directions: In layers, place all ingredients in order given into big roasting pan with cover (or use aluminum foil).
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Do not open oven door until done.
Do not mix. Very important!
Do not peek!!

title: fried plantains(wild bananas)
directions: Peel and slice plantains into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place a little vegetable oil in a frying pan and heat on medium flame.
Add plantain slices in single layer.
Cook until browned on both sides. Serve with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Cook in skillet.
Get oil hot and then add the squash.
Cook fast and keep stirred.
It will brown a little.
When cooked, the cheese may be added.
Add salt and black pepper.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Serve with fruit slices.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle chicken, then mushrooms, onions, cheese and salt in pie pan.
Put remainder of ingredients into blender or food processor.
Process 15 seconds until smooth (you may use an electric mixer).
Pour blended mixture evenly over cheese in pie pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chinese hash
directions: Brown beef.
Mix together all but noodles.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° with lid. Remove lid. Bake 30 minutes more.
Add Chinese noodles and bake 15 more minutes, no lid.

title: cooked pinto beans for 100
directions: Cook
at
400° in large roaster.
Cook about 4 hours or until soft.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
While hot, stir in 1 pint orange sherbet.
Add mandarin oranges, crushed pineapple and pineapple tidbits.
Stir and chill.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; cream.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk and soda; combine, then add jam (your choice, blackberry, strawberry).
Add nuts and raisins.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour in
3 (9-inch) pans; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
(Do not beat.)
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and garlic in salt water until tender.
Drain well.
Add 1/2 stick light butter.
Using hand blender mash all above ingredients until smooth.
Slowly add skim milk and 2 Tablespoons lite mayo, until creamy consistency.
Sprinkle parsley before serving.

title: quick onion bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place dough in greased pan or cookie sheet and shape into an oblong about an inch thick and 8 to 9 inches long.
Brush top with soft butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown on top.

title: strawberry cups
directions: In largest bowl, stir together sugar, apricots (quartered with syrup), crushed pineapple (with juice), strawberries (halved), bananas (sliced) and grapes (halved). Spoon into clear plastic cups, filling each with juice. Garnish with coconut. Freeze. Thaw 1 hour before serving frozen.

title: poor man cake
directions: Cook raisins in the water for 5 minutes; then let cool.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add flour, baking soda, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add raisins and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Any good frosting is good on this cake.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa to a boil in saucepan. Boil for 30 seconds.
Immediately pour over oatmeal that has been combined with vanilla and powdered sugar.
Quickly mix together and drop cookies onto wax paper.
Makes 3 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: date squares
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water and simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.

title: chili
directions: In chili kettle, over medium heat, saut beef, stirring occasionally, until red color disappears. Keep ground beef in small chunks. Pour off fat. Add onions, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, oregano, basil, red pepper and cumin; mix well. Cook, stirring, until onions and green pepper are tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in sugar, salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Mix well. Bring to boiling, breaking up tomatoes with a fork. Simmer slowly covered, stirring occasionally until thick and flavors are blended, about 40 minutes. Add beans; simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until hot. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spices, sauce and mushrooms. Boil noodles and drain.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, sour cream and cheese twice.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order listed in a medium casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese. Let set in oven until cheese melts.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg. Shape into 6 patties.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown half of the patties on both sides.
Set aside. Spoon off fat and repeat with remaining patties.
In same skillet, combine rest of soup and mushrooms. Heat to boiling and return patties to skillet. Reduce heat. Cover.
Cook patties until done or no longer pink.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs.
Dissolve soda in 1 tablespoon liquid (juice or water).
Add shortening to bananas and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, soda, eggs and nuts.
Stir only until mixed.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook; add salt if desired.
Cool. Pour salad dressing over potatoes; toss lightly.
Put in refrigerator while mixing the mashed eggs, mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Add bacon bits and onion.
Fold this mixture in potatoes; sprinkle with paprika.
Chill for 10 to 12 hours. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: s & w bean soup
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix well together the soup, sour cream and poppy seed; add to chicken, which has been cut into small pieces.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt the margarine; crumble in the crackers and put over top of chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cranberry festive bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Combine buttermilk, oil, eggs and orange rind; stir well. Add to dry ingredients; beat until smooth. Fold in cranberries, dates and walnuts. (Batter will be thick.)

title: simple deviled crabs
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add flour.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add milk; cook until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients (except crumbs).
Mix well; pour into greased casserole dish or individual shells.
Top with breadcrumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: cool chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in microwave. Watch every 30 seconds until melted. Careful not to burn. Fold in Cool Whip (for fuller mixture, use electric
mixer or add more Cool Whip). Spread into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: apricot chicken with rice
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of 10 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix dry onion soup mix, apricot preserves and salad dressing. Using half of this mixture, stir in 2 1/2 cups water.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice and brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed (small pieces).
Spread enough mayo to make 1-inch thick on top.
Sprinkle top with sugar. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle on bacon bits.
Chill for 8 hours.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Get ready-to-eat biscuits from baker section.
Slice biscuits; leave bottom in pan.
Spread mixture on biscuits.
Put cubed ham on top.
Put top of biscuits on.
Bake 10 minutes at 300°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in a large serving bowl.
In a small bowl, mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss gently, but thoroughly, to blend.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: banana frosting
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, vanilla and about 1/3 of the sugar. Add more sugar to thicken if frosting is thin.
Mix well.

title: lazy man's holupschi
directions: Fry ground beef in oil for 1 or 2 min.
Add onion, salt, pepper, and rice.
Mix well while gently sauteing for 2 or 3 min. Add soup and water.
Mix well.
Turn cabbage into greased baking dish.
Pour mixture over raw cabbage.
Do not stir.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hrs. at 325°F.

title: no peek stew
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Combine next 4 dry ingredients and sprinkle over layers.
Pour V-8 juice over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours. Don't peek!

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir into milk the juice of 2 lemons and 2 egg yolks.
Pour into vanilla wafer crumb crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add vanilla and sugar.
Mix and pour over pie filling.
Bake at 350° just until meringue is browned.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and rice in bowl.
Grease a casserole dish.
Pour soup in dish.
Place chicken breast on top of soup.
Put pat of butter on top of each breast.
Cook in 250° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1/4 of the soup with remaining ingredients except water; mix well.
Shape into six patties, arrange in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water.
Spoon over patties.
Return to oven; bake 10 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix together.
Put
batter
in greased and floured tube pan.
Mix
tablespoons
cinnamon
and
cup sugar. Sprinkle 1/2 mixture on batter in pan and swirl.
Pour rest of batter in pan.
Sprinkle
rest
of
mixture
and swirl again. Bake at 325° for
1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave in oven for 10 minutes or bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: snow white fudge
directions: Combine sugar,
butter and milk.
Bring to rolling boil over medium
heat,
whisking
constantly
to avoid scorching. Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream. Stir until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla, stir until blended. Pour into
a buttered
8-inch square pan.
Place on wire rack and cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield 3 pounds.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls onto a 11 x 17-inch cookie pan. Pat together to make a thin crust all over the pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing. Blend until creamy. Spread over crust.
Use food processor or grate veggies very fine.
Sprinkle on top of cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening, add sugar gradually and beat until light.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and creamed mixture, add corn flakes.
Drop small teaspoons on greased baking sheet, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until delicately browned.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: aunt gen's barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Mix sauce and pour over chops.
Cover. Cook for 1 1/2 hours. Last 20 minutes, remove cover and turn chops until sauce is absorbed.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Peel, core and cube apples.
Place in shallow rectangular baking dish.
Spread with half the sugar.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, salt and pecans.
Cut butter into mixture with pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread over apples, pressing down over and around edges so topping completely covers apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir peanuts, sugar, syrups and salt together in deep bowl. Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir candy so all sugar is mixed and continue cooking on High 3 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Cook on High 1 to 3 minutes.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour immediately onto lightly buttered surface, spreading it out.
Cool and break into pieces. Store in airtight container.
If roasted, salted peanuts are used, don't salt and add peanuts after first 4 minutes of cooking.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove.
Add jello; dissolve, then add 2 cups cold water.
Put in refrigerator; let set (barely jell).
Take out.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and cheese. Pour into dish; let set until jello sets.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In large, heavy skillet or wok, cook chicken, onions and mushrooms in oil over high heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes, or until mushrooms are golden.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 3 minutes longer, until heated through and well blended. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: In 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan, simmer apples, water and sugar in 350° oven.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; stir in flour, salt and pepper and cook until smooth.
Add milk and chicken stock.
Cook until thick like gravy.
Add lemon juice and chicken.
Add carrots, onions, celery and English peas.
Place in baking dish.

title: lace dosai
directions: Mix ingredients together and make sure there are no lumps. Heat grill; grease with butter.
Pour batter and cook like pancakes.
Serve with Coconut Chutney.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla and oil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.

title: taffy dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Top with nuts and serve with fruit.

title: babka
directions: Pour warm water over yeast to dissolve.
Meanwhile, scald milk and melt butter and sugar in it.
When cool, add the flour, eggs (which have been beaten), yeast, salt and lemon extract.
Beat well.
Put in warm place to raise twice the size.
Then put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Grind the cranberries. Cut your oranges real fine (peel).
Mix all together.
Dissolve your Jell-O in the hot water and pour over the other ingredients. Refrigerate until it sets.

title: grandma's hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly with fork.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool; frost.

title: micro turkey loaves
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, milk, poultry seasoning and garlic salt.
Add turkey; mix well.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Arrange around edges of 1 3/4-quart casserole dish. Micro covered 7 to 9 minutes until no longer pink.
Spoon over loaves barbecue sauce before serving.

title: fast lasagne
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and microwave on High for 7 minutes until bubbly.

title: burritos
directions: Cook everything except cheese for 18 to 24 hours on low in crock-pot.
Tear roast apart in the crock-pot.
Add cheese on bottom of tortillas.
Add cooked ingredients and wrap.
Pour excess gravy juice on top and bake at 350° until the cheese melts. Add more cheese on top if desired.
Individual, unbaked burritos can be wrapped and frozen for later use if desired.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in sour milk.
Beat eggs, brown sugar and shortening.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lo-cal taco dip
directions: Blend sour cream with taco seasoning.
Put in a wide bowl. Top with shredded cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl. Mix butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola; bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture, then mix. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows; beat. The batter will be thin and the marshmallows will rise to the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).

title: potluck hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Mix together cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle cornflakes and margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nestle quik cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil together.
Mix in buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients and milk mixture alternately together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan lightly greased and floured.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Remove from oven and poke holes in it with a straw.	Pour can of sweetened milk and caramel topping over cake. Let cool. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath or Skor bars.

title: rhubarb nutmeg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs and cream, add sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Pour over shell 3/4 full of cut rhubarb.
Bake 50 - 60 minutes in 375° oven.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add ginger ale.
Stir.
Chill until nearly set.
Add other ingredients.
Mix.
Chill until firm. This recipe can be reduced in calories by using sugar-free jello and diet ginger ale.
Also, 1/2 package plain gelatin dissolved in a bit of ginger ale and stirred into hot water will make for a firmer salad.
If you like a stronger ginger flavor, use 2 cups ginger ale and no water.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, reserving a small portion of the grated Cheddar cheese on the side.
Put mixture into a casserole dish and sprinkle reserved sharp Cheddar on top. Bake in oven for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast cereal cookies
directions: Cream Butter Buds, both sugars, Egg Beaters and vanilla with hand mixer until smooth.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda and baking powder.
Stir in oats, Tripletts and Grape-Nuts.
Add raisins, if desired.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a baking sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot meat or vegetables in boiling stew.
(Do not drop onto liquid.)
Cook over low heat, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Yields 10 to 12 dumplings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble cookies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Prepare pudding according to directions and pour over cookies. Top with whipped topping.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: kiss-kiss cookies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, butter and chocolate; add eggs one at a time until well blended. Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add gradually to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition. Cover and chill overnight.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into confectioners sugar, coating lightly, then shape into a pointed kiss.
Place on greased baking sheet 2-inches apart and bake for 12 to 14 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: virginia's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce and jelling agent together. Add remaining ingredients. Boil 1 to 2 minutes. Put in jars; seal.

title: swedish cream
directions: Add all ingredients except berries and heat to boiling (just the first 4 ingredients).

title: peach turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly, then add milk to make dough soft.
Place dough on a cutting board and knead gently 30 seconds.

Divide dough in half and roll one half at a time into a rectangle, approximately 6 x 8 inches, about 1/4 inch thick. Cut each of these into 4 smaller rectangles, about 6 x 3 inches. Place slices of peaches on half of each rectangle, dot with margarine, and sprinkle with sugar.
Then fold these over and gently pinch turnover closed. Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 8 turnovers.

title: mac salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Drain and cool.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight or at least 2 hours before serving.

title: tuna fruit salad
directions: Mound attractively in lettuce lined bowls.
Toss together unpeeled apples, cut in 1/2-inch cubes, 4 cups torn lettuce, tuna (drained and flaked) and grapes.
Cover and chill.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Toss with tuna mixture.
Serves 6.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Makes about 2 quarts.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps about 2 weeks.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Cut Crisco in with 2 knives or pastry blender until like coarse meal. Add milk; mix with fork or hand. Knead on lightly floured board 8 to 10 times. Roll or pat out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake on baking sheet at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate lover's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream butter, gradually adding sugars and beating until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes. Blend in vanilla, egg and sour cream.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix with rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cool, frost with Watergate Icing.

title: cocoa-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt and milk in a medium saucepan and bring to a boil on stove.
When mixture comes to a soft ball, remove from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour onto a greased plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up bundt cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco together.
Add eggs and mix well. Add flour and lemon.
Fold in 7-Up and mix until you have a smooth batter. (Hint:
When measuring 7-Up, try to pour it really easy without making too much fizz.
Also, when pouring into mixture, make sure you pour very easy and fold gently.)
Pour mixture into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: In resealable plastic bag or large bowl, combine all vegetables.
Toss well. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
(Can mix dressing in a jar and shake vigorously to blend.)
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate at least one hour to allow flavors to blend.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onion.
Put in pan with 1/2 cup water.
Add butter and salt.
Boil until tender.
Do not drain. Add cheese, stir until cheese melts, add sour cream.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for sauce.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan the broccoli which has been partially thawed, chicken and sauce. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery, mayonnaise, onion and mushroom soup.
Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herbed stuffing mix that has been combined with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Cook all ingredients together. Season to taste. Add 1 1/2 cups rice (raw). Stir until well coated. Add 5 bouillon cubes dissolved in 4 cups hot water. Boil for 5 minutes. Then cover and simmer 1 hour or until done.

title: microwave beets
directions: Wash fresh beets well and remove stem and root ends.
Place beets in a 2-quart microwave dish with water to cover.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes on full power.
When beets can be easily pierced with a sharp knife, drain and peel off skins.
Serve whole or diced.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in bananas.
Grease and lightly flour bread pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: do ahead brunch eggs
directions: *May substitute margarine for butter, evaporated skim milk for evaporated milk and 2 egg whites for each whole egg.

title: stove top potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove bacon from pan.
Saute onion until golden brown.
Add sugar, flour, vinegar and water slowly until thick.
Pour over drained potatoes.
Crumble bacon and add to potato salad.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Combine water and apples in microwave dish.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add sugar and cinnamon.

title: guacamole(avocado dip)
directions: Peel and mash the avocados.
Mix well with all the other ingredients.
Pile into a serving dish with an avocado pit in the center.
This is supposed to keep the guacamole from turning dark. Makes about 2 or 3 cups.
Serve with fried tortilla triangles.

title: spiced green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes, but do not peel.
If small tomatoes are used, prick them slightly.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Pour mixture over tomatoes.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight.
Drain and cook fluid until it coats a spoon.
Add tomatoes and cook until clear.
Put into canning jars and seal. This can also be done with plums, pears or peaches.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients and chips last.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet for 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Leave on cookie sheet until cold.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/3-inch slices.
Mix water, eggs and salt.
Dip eggplant in flour, then in eggs, then in bread crumbs.
Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in large skillet over moderate heat.
Cook eggplant until lightly browned on both sides.
Add remaining olive oil as needed.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients until smoothly blended.
If too soft, refrigerate until semi-firm.
Form a ball on cheese plate or tray, using spoon and/or knife to create symmetrical shape.
You may decorate with parsley flakes or chopped pecans.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, Karo, shortening and eggs and blend well. Add soda, baking powder, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add milk and flour until well blended.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine shortening, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla and beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats and dry ingredients.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mama ann's upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in baking dish in 325° oven.
Beat well sugar and eggs; stir milk in good; stir half at a time.
Mix well flour, salt, peach or cherry pie filling.
Take baking dish with melted butter; pour can of fruit and juice all over baking dish.
Then take batter and pour slowly all over fruit.
Spread over Pyrex dish and bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Durkee onions.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown soup
directions: Pour chicken broth in a pot; bring to boil, then put in hash browns. Cook until tender, then add cream of chicken soup. Stir until blended. Cut Velveeta into small blocks and add to soup. Stir until melted. Fry bacon and crumble on top of soup. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute the squash in a little vegetable oil over medium heat until it has completely broken down, about 15 to 20 minutes. Line a colander with a clean tea towel. Place the cooked squash in the lined colander. Squeeze excess moisture from the squash. Set aside.

title: monterey chicken phyllo appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine chicken, cheese, onions and parsley flakes; mix well.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Pour off cherry juice and reserve.
Quarter cherries.
Stir in sugar and butter.
Pour in orange, cherry juice and water.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add a small amount at a time to your mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Glaze with powdered sugar, milk mixture.
Decorate with chopped cherries and pecans.

title: holiday nuts 'n' spice cookies
directions: Finely chop 1 1/2 cups of nuts.
Combine flour, chopped nuts and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Blend all well and then bake in casserole dish 45 to 55 minutes at 350° or until it's set.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together cheese, 1/2 oleo and vanilla. Alternately beat in sugar and 1/3 cup milk. Blend in chocolate. Remove 2 cups for frosting; cover and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in 1 cup powdered sugar or more and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla.

title: herbed meat loaf
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine egg, stuffing mix, milk, onion soup mix and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce; add ground beef and mix well. Shape into loaf and put in meat loaf pan. Drizzle 1/4 cup barbecue sauce over meat. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: 5 hour beef sandwiches
directions: Put all ingredients, except buns, in large covered kettle. Cook 5 hours at 350°, stirring every hour.
Serve on buns.
Serves 16.

title: apple surprise
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Put in a glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: roasted pepper salad
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place peppers on broiler pan and roast until they turn light brown; keep turning peppers over until brown on all sides.
When roasted, peel skins off and take out seeds. Cut in strips.
Place in dish and sprinkle with salt.
Add parsley, garlic and vinegar.
Stir and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
This gives the peppers and flavoring a change to settle.

title: cheese toasties
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, milk, onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and paprika.
Mix well.
Toast English muffins until crisp in a toaster.
Brown bacon in skillet and drain off fat.
Crumble bacon.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture on each half slice of muffin.
Cut each slice into 4 wedges.
Sprinkle on bacon.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 Cheese Toasties.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and place milk, sugar, salt and shortening in saucepan and heat until lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour.
Mix well and cover.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls with well greased hands.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat 2 eggs slightly.
Add sour cream.
Mix.
Add corn and Mazola.
Mix well.
Add to meal.
Bake in greased 7 x 11-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Check after 20 minutes to see if heat is correct.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix well.
Form into balls.
Dip in sugar and press into mint mold.
Let dry several hours on waxed paper, sprinkled with sugar. Yields 90 or 250 mints.

title: lemon curd tart filling
directions: This sauce can be used for French toast, thumbprint cookies, etc.
Enjoy.

title: sweet n' sour sausage balls
directions: Make 1-inch sausage balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garden vegetable dish
directions: Dice all these vegetables together about the same size each according to how much you want to make.
Salt lightly; stir together.
Pour hot vegetable oil over and let set 30 minutes.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Salt and pepper and slightly brown chicken; put in a casserole.
Stir other ingredients in drippings of breast.
Bring to a boil and pour over breast.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's pork dressing
directions: Boil pork steaks.
Pinch toasted bread, onion and sage in bowl. Then pour the water off of the steaks, over the bread mixture to make it moist.
Then put mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake until brown.

title: daisy's pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Beat the egg.
Add pineapple juice (about 1/2 cup), lemon juice and dash of salt.
Cook over low heat until it starts to bubble.
Remove from heat; keep stirring.
Pour over other ingredients.
Really good!

title: manicotti
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Cool.
Stir in cheese.
Stir in crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season to taste.
Cook manicotti shells according to package directions (don't overcook).
Stuff shells with meat, handling carefully.
Spoon 1/2 of spaghetti sauce over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange shells on top of sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil, place crackers.
Melt butter and sugar; cook until boils.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir constantly. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until dark brown in color.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 12 ounce package of milk chocolate chips; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread chocolate, then sprinkle with walnuts.
Pan size 15 1/4 x 10 1/4-inches.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Combine soup and cheese over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients to stir until mixture is hot.
Use toast points for dipping.

title: raspberry mousse
directions: Dissolve jello in warm cranberry juice.
Add cranberry sauce to warm mixture, breaking it into small chunks.
Chill mixture for about 45 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: almost! better than money cake
directions: Follow cake mix directions; bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, use handle of wooden spoon and poke holes every inch or so.
Pour the caramel ice cream topping over; let cool.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with crushed Heath bars on top.

title: doyle's dilly of a fish
directions: Melt butter and add lemon juice.
Thinly slice onion and diced green pepper.
Place fish in a buttered glass baking dish.
Brush with lemon butter and sprinkle with dill.
Spread tomatoes over filets and add pinch of sugar.
Spread onion and green pepper next. Pour remainder of lemon butter over top.
Sprinkle dill over all. Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: rigatoni with shrimp and feta cheese(serves 8)
directions: In a kettle, cook onion and garlic in oil over medium heat until softened.
Add wine and boil mixture for 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with juice, 1 tablespoon parsley, basil, oregano and salt.
Simmer mixture 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until reduced and thickened somewhat.
Add shrimp and cook for 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp are just firm.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix well and shake. Add 2 teaspoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.

title: grape-pear chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with veal, turkey or ham.

title: grape tapioca
directions: Add tapioca to boiling water.
Boil 15 minutes. Turn off heat and cover 15 minutes.
Then add sugar.
Last add jello.
Add fruit of any flavor; if grape, add grapes.

title: chocolate walnut pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, spice, baking soda and baking powder.
Add pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
Beat to blend thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Level top.
Bake at 350° for one hour until loaf is lightly browned and springy to touch.
Cool.

title: mother's english coffee cookies
directions: Combine Spry and sugar.
Add coffee, eggs and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Makes a stiff dough.
Try a sample cookie.
Add a little more flour, if needed.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 360° until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans. Shape into a ball and chill overnight. Roll in pecans before serving.

title: cranberry fruit punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice cocktail and orange, lemon and pineapple juices.
Mix well with sugar and water.
Pour over ice. Ready to serve.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda, sugar and baking powder.
Add coconut, chopped nuts, oatmeal and brown sugar.
Work in butter. Add eggs and vanilla.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Mix all ingredients. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes. Do not overcook!

title: jello surprise
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions.
Let set overnight. Just before serving prepare Dream Whip.
Stir into Jell-O along with your favorite fruit and the marshmallows.
My favorite bananas.

title: cream cheese finger cookies
directions: In bowl, cream butter and cream cheese.
Beat in extract. Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture and creamed mixture together.
Stir in pecans.
Shape into 2-inches logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Roll warm cookies into confectioners sugar.
Yield: 2 dozen cookies.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: pizza(my own recipe)
directions: Soak yeast in water for 5 minutes.
Add salt, oregano, oil and cheese.
Stir to mix well. Add flour.
Stir with fork until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board. Knead until elastic.
Cover with warmed pan for 10 minutes.

title: alfajores(dedicated to helen corley)
directions: Open the top of the can of milk, but leave the lid closed. Place the full can in a water bath; boil gently until the milk caramelizes (about 2 hours).
Watch it carefully.
Let the caramel cool in the can.

title: spaghetti with broccoli
directions: Peel broccoli stems; cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Break flowerets into small pieces.
Set aside.
In a 10-inch fry pan, heat 4 tablespoons oil.
Add 1/4 cup parsley and garlic.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes without browning.
Add tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add all herbs.
Lower heat to simmer for 30 minutes, partially covered.
In a small skillet, brown pinenuts in 2 tablespoons oil until it browns.
Set aside.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Beat oil, eggs, sugar and buttermilk together.
Add spices, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and apples; mix well.
Add nuts.
Use 2 loaf pans, lightly greased, and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in large bowl.
Fold in pineapple, zucchini and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; do not cook too soft.
Cool; peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and butter.
Stir occasionally until cheese is almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a full boil over medium heat. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently and watching to make sure candy does not burn. Reduce heat if necessary. Remove from heat and let cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Stir until candy starts to set. Pour into buttered dish. Cool in refrigerator until completely set. Cut into squares.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, butter, water and molasses.
Sift together the remaining ingredients and add to first mixture. Chill well.
Roll out or make into balls and press with glass. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut
cookie
dough
in 1/2-inch slices.
Line pizza pan overlapping slightly. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.	Cool.

title: german cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage, bell pepper and onion.
Pour vegetable oil and sugar mixed together over cabbage mixture.

title: unbaked pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Mix together. Heat in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Put filling in pie crust; top with whipped topping.

title: tallarene
directions: Brown onion and beef in hot oil.
Add soup, water, salt, noodles, corn and olives; mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover; cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, or until noodles are tender.

title: spaghetti parmesan
directions: In saucepot, prepare spaghetti as label directs; drain. Return spaghetti to saucepot.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, cook hamburger and onion, stirring occasionally until all pan juices evaporate and meat is browned.
Add corn, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, sugar and cinnamon; heat through.
Toss spaghetti with Parmesan cheese and butter.
Arrange spaghetti on warm platter.
Spoon meat mixture over spaghetti. Serves 6.

title: sour cream raisin pudding
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven until set (20 to 25 minutes).
This can be baked in a crust and topped with Cool Whip.

title: real good bran muffins
directions: Soak all bran in milk.	Cream butter, brown sugar, eggs and salt.
Add	flour,	molasses and baking soda in hot water. Add all bran
mixture and dates or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes
about 40 medium muffins.
Dough can be put in icebox a few days
to
bake
later.
Muffins
can
also	be frozen.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: You will need a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crawfish or shrimp casserole in a rice cooker
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; then transfer into rice cooker.
After bell rings, wait 10 minutes and then serve.

title: joe's delight
directions: Dice and boil potatoes.
Brown and crumble hamburger meat. Pour 1/2 water off cooked potatoes.
Pour in green beans, hamburger and soup.
Cook until soup is hot.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle flattened chicken breasts with salt, black and cayenne pepper and parsley flakes.
Place 1 slice of dried beef or ham on top of each breast, trimming to fit.
Roll breasts and place seam side down in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Remove breasts to heated platter.
Stir sour cream into sauce. To serve, pour sauce over chicken and rice or pasta.

title: health punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except ginger ale) in large container. Just before serving, add ice ring of your choice.
Pour chilled ginger ale over all.
Loaded with vitamins A and C.
Makes approximately 100 (4 ounce) servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven. This can be made and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually add dry ingredients; stir in pumpkin.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Top with crushed nuts.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Turn out on cloth covered with confectioners sugar.
Roll up in cloth (dish towel works well).
Let set until cool.
Unroll; spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll and chill.

title: tomatoes fines herbes
directions: Arrange tomato slices in serving dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Let stand at room temperature at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in a medium skillet; cover over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally. Drain well. Line bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, pressing firmly perforations to seal. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over sausage. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan-custard pie
directions: *First, toast 1 cup of pecans in oven at 350° for approximately 8 minutes; stir once.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs slightly in shallow bowl.
Add salt and milk.
Dip each piece of bread into egg mixture.
Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Place slices of egg-coated bread in butter and cook until golden brown, turning once.
Serve immediately with syrup or lightly dusted with powdered sugar.

title: cheeseburger and tater tot casserole
directions: For variation, you may add 1 can French-cut green beans and omit cheese.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and beat well.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into greased pan (may sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts on top).
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes until toothpick test; cool.
Let stand 6 hours before slicing.
Eat rest of the bag of chocolate chips.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, cracker crumbs, onion and the 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt oregano and pepper.
Shape into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Roll up and press ends to seal.
(Seal very carefully.)
Place in a shallow pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Pour the 2/3 cup of sauce over the top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Strip bacon across top of beans and bake until desired thickness at 325° or until onion is done.

title: sweet carrot casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushroom caps clean.
Melt 4 tablespoons oleo; let cool a bit.
Use hands and coat caps well with oleo.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Mix crumbs, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and egg together.
Fill each cap with mixture.
Melt remaining oleo. Sprinkle caps with Parmesan and drizzle with oleo.
Bake
in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.
Very good.

title: banana nut oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the dry ingredients in large bowl. Mix milk, bananas, egg whites and oil together.
Add the dry ingredients to liquid and mix.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups or spray with Pam baking spray.
Fill each cup with batter. Bake for 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Cook until well blended.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts.
Beat yolks.
Add to cheese mixture.
Stir in the crab mixture.
Bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add corned beef and heat. Stir in flour and egg. Blend. Add chopped kraut and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until thick. Cover and chill overnight.
The next day, form mixture into small balls.
Dip first into flour, then into beaten egg, and then into fine cracker crumbs. Fry in hot deep fat until golden brown.
If desired, cook in advance and reheat at serving time, 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: beer bread(muffins)
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and pour in greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cajun party mix
directions: Combine the cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Pour into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over cereal mixture and stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 40 to 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together ingredients. Store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
Also a great cold weather drink.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Over medium heat, steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Turn off heat, cool and press dry.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs and milk until frothy.
In separate bowl, thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion; spoon into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, spreading evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand 5 minutes and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Yield:
4 dozen 1 1/4-inch squares.

title: sumter salad dressing(from barbara's downstairs tea room)
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve over spinach salad made of spinach leaves, chopped eggs, crumbled, cooked bacon and sliced fresh mushrooms.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: In saucepan, brown both meats and drain.
Mix in spaghetti sauce and spices.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
In 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan, spread 1/4 of the meat sauce.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese (alternating layers).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: green bean and snow pea salad
directions: Bring water and 1 teaspoon salt to boil.
Add green beans and cook 2 minutes.
Add snow peas and cook 30 seconds.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Whisk vinegar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in bowl.
Add oil and whisk thoroughly.
Add beans, peas and onion/pepper.
Toss, coating all ingredients. Serve at room temperature.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Place ground beef in 4-quart saucepan; brown in oil.
Add garlic and oregano.
Place frozen spinach on top of beef on medium heat until spinach thaws.
Pour in mushrooms (drained).
Pour in cheese.
Mix all together.
Turn off heat.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Add to mixture and stir.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked onions
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 1-quart saucepan, at medium heat, add butter, honey and salt.
In greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange onion slices, pour honey mixture over onions.
Bake for 45 minutes until onions are fork tender and golden brown.
Vidalia onions are best.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain fruit, saving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix fruit and cheese.
Combine flour and sugar; mix with fruit mixture.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix butter and crackers until crumbly; spread over top.
Pour remaining juice over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Brush mayonnaise on each piece of chicken, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place in foiled 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with foil. Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: my favorite bread pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, eggs and sugar until smooth. Add evaporated milk, whole milk and vanilla. Cut French bread into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with tap water (avoid soaking). With large spoon, stir into bread pieces the egg and milk mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until nicely browned.
Delicious hot or cold, alone or with someone.

title: raspberry souffle
directions: Thaw berries (reserve some for garnish, wrap in foil and return to freezer).
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine raspberries, gelatin, 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice.
Heat to dissolve gelatin.
Add almond extract and cool this until consistency of egg whites.
Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Whip cream; reserve 1/4 cup.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into raspberries.
Pour into 1-quart souffle dish which may be extended with a wax paper collar.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with whipped cream and reserved berries.

title: homemade subs
