directions: Place bread on baking sheet and spray bread with cooking oil and sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Bake as directed.
Let cool. Slice bread open and pour Italian dressing on both sides of bread, then layer ham, cheese, roast beef, lettuce and tomato. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Makes about 16 subs.
May also use your favorite meats.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Cook tortillas in hot oil (about 15 seconds on each side). Place 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon onion on each and roll. Place in flat 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Saute 1/4 cup onion in oil or oleo. Add flour and stir in broth.
Cook until thick. Add sour cream and chiles. Continue cooking until this is heated. Pour mixture over rolled tortillas. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips into a casserole dish. Top with chips.
Cook at 350° to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly and done!

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add onion soup and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir until thickened.
Spoon over hamburger buns.

title: salsa dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate. Dip with your favorite taco chips or fresh vegetables.

title: o'ma's pie crust
directions: Mix. Put in pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all by hand, not a mixer.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut deveined livers in half and cook in oil over medium heat until no longer red.
Remove skillet.
Add soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic.
Let cool.
Combine one piece of liver with a water chestnut half; roll bacon round the two and secure with toothpick. Broil when ready to serve until bacon is crisp.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar; save 3/4 cup for topping and put rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and pour in 1 baked pie shell.

title: 1890 chicken and macaroni supper
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until almost tender, about 12 minutes; drain.
Place 1/3 of macaroni on bottom of 2-quart lightly greased casserole.
Top with 1/2 the chicken pieces; dot chicken with 1/2 the butter, salt, pepper and 1/2 the chicken broth.
Repeat layers ending with remaining 1/3 of macaroni on top.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hot ham sandwiches for a crowd
directions: Make a paste of margarine, onion, poppy seeds, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread the paste on the cut surfaces of both halves of each bun.
Stack ham and cheese equally on the 10 buns. Wrap each sandwich in completely in a square of aluminum foil and place on a cookie sheet.
At this point, the sandwiches may be kept in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours.
Bake sandwiches for 20 minutes at 275°.
May be doubled.
Serves 10.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Grate cheeses.
Mix in flour and slightly beaten eggs.
Add milk and butter.
Mix.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: I was walking down life's highway a long time ago.
One day, I saw a sign that read "Heaven's Grocery Store."
As I got a little closer the door came open wide and when I came to myself, I was standing inside.
I saw a host of angels.
They were standing everywhere.
Everything a Christian needed was in that grocery store and all you couldn't carry you could come back the next day for more.
First I got some patience.
Love was in the same row; further down was understanding - you need that everywhere you go. I got a box or two of wisdom and a bag or two of faith.
I just couldn't miss the Holy Spirit for He was all over the place.
I stopped to get some strength and courage to help me run the race. By then, my basket was getting full, but I remembered I needed some grace.
I didn't forget salvation, for salvation was free, so I tried to get enough of that to save both you and me.
Then I started up to the counter to pay my grocery bill, for I thought I had everything to do my Master's will.
As I went up the aisle, I saw a prayer and I just had to put it in, for I knew when I stepped outside, I would run into sin.
Peace and joy were plentiful, they were on the last shelf.
Song and praise were hanging near, so I just helped myself.
Then I said to the angel, "How much do I owe?" He just smiled and said, "Just take them everywhere you go." Again, I smiled at him and said, "How much do I really owe?"
He smiled again and said, "My child, Jesus paid your bill a long time ago."

title: edible aquarium(children's recipe)
directions: First, dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
If mixture is still thin, refrigerate until slightly thickened.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix strawberries and jello; set aside.
Mix pudding with milk. After it thickens, add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, strawberries and pudding mix in a deep dish.

title: oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: In saucepan, put butter, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Heat to rolling boil. Cook 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal; mix in vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Eat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle half on bottom of pan. Cook sliced squash 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix soup, carrots and sour cream.
Place layer of squash over buttered bread crumbs and then the soup mixture.
Alternate layers.
Sprinkle top with remaining bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in water and bouillon cube until soft.
Melt oleo and add onions, cubed cheese, milk and sour cream.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour over carrots.
Place in greased casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ernie's pork and corn stuffing bake
directions: Do not use fewer chops as the moisture from the chops is required for the stuffing and to sufficiently cover the stuffing when cooking to hold in the moisture.

title: spinach frittata
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and pour into baking dish. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
To make individual servings, bake in muffin pans.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oil together. Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with water.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° about 1 hour until tests done with a toothpick.
Let stand 10 minutes. Turn from pan to cool.

title: my favorite stew
directions: Brown meat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook all day!

title: munch mix
directions: Combine butter and dressing mix. Stir in nuts, pretzel and cereal. Microwave on high for 2 min. (heat through). Serve warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini about 5 minutes. Saute carrots and onions in 4 tablespoons butter.
Mix zucchini, carrots, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix and pour into a baking dish. Saute 1 cup stuffing mix with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: breakfast cinnamon pinwheels
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead together 1/2 minute.
Roll oblong to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with soft margarine.
Stir cinnamon, sugar and nuts together.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up tightly like a jelly roll.
Cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Arrange cut side down on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. (While still hot, frost with thin powdered sugar icing.)
Best served warm.

title: nut crunch
directions: Place nuts in shallow baking dish.
Toast in preheated 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and salt.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts.
Melt butter in jelly roll pan; spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°, stirring every 10 minutes. Makes about 4 cups.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve jello and gelatin in 1/4 cup hot water.
Add to pineapple mixture and cool. Add cherries, nuts, bananas and coconut.
Put into 3 baked pie shells and put in refrigerator to set for 1 hour or more.
Serve with whipped cream!

title: emma's cottage cheese salad
directions: Pour cottage cheese into a mixing bowl, add dry jello and fruit. This makes enough salad to refill the containers.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until crisp, drain.
Place in 1-quart casserole. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish sauce and pepper.
Mix with carrots.
Mix cracker crumbs with oleo.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the items listed.
Chill and serve.

title: pink cloud congealed salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple.
Add jello and mix well.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add cream cheese, softened and blended with the milk.
Fold in Cool Whip or prepared Dream Whip.

title: new england christmas eve seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook seafoods and peas.
Cut scallops in half, also shrimp if they are large.
Cook rice 30 minutes. Saute green pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Mix together mayonnaise, curry powder and worcestershire.
Combine with peas, seafood, salt and pepper.
Place in lightly greased 3 qt. casserole and bake for 35 minutes.

title: orient-fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into frying parts.
Mix flour and seasonings together in a bag.
Shake well.
In a large frying pan, melt margarine on low heat.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bambino's
directions: Place Melba toast rounds on tray.
Squeeze a blob of ketchup (nickle size) on each round.
Take oregano and sprinkle over whole tray of rounds.
Proceed by putting a slice of pepperoni on rounds, gently pushing it down so that ketchup spreads it out without running over the edge.
Then sprinkle 3 to 4 pieces of grated Mozzarella on each slice of pepperoni.
Put in 400° oven for 1 1/2 minutes.
Make sure cheese is fully melted.
Serve immediately and enjoy.

title: laura's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and stir well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan and spread to cover the bottom evenly.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes.
This is a semi-fluffy, yet chewy brownie about 1 inch thick.
For a thicker, chewier brownie add less water, using just enough to mix well.
Do not overcook or it will be hard and dry.

title: fruit fix
directions: Put all fruits in a large pot.
Cover with apple juice, add cinnamon.
Cook on medium-low until fruit is soft.
Puree fruit mixture in food processor until smooth. Store in refrigerator in a mason jar.
Use on crackers, toast, in plain yogurt, oatmeal, anything you'd use preserves for.
This is a very good source of Bioflavonoid and Vitamin C.

title: "gooey" butter cake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of oblong pan:
butter or oleo, cake mix and eggs.
Blend the following on low speed in mixer and pour over the mixture:
2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter flavoring.
Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheeses.
Mix all ingredients together.
This makes 2 balls.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add pepper, onion and mushroom soup.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add pepperoni and beef mixture. Stir in spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add salad dressing, water and vanilla.
Beat at medium or high speed until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or dish in oven.
Mix biscuit mix, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken.
Place in pan, skin sides down.
Bake 35 minutes and turn.
Bake until tender, about 15 more minutes.

title: quick deli dills
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Put dill in bottom of crock.
Put garlic in bottom of crock.
Put pickles on top.
Add boiling brine to cover cukes.
Put a plate over cukes to hold them under the brine.
Cover crock with a towel.
Check in 3 to 4 days to see if they look like pickles.
Put in jars and cover with the brine.
Store in fridge.

title: mixed vegetable dish
directions: Combine ingredients and put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with croutons and sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie(for chocolate lovers!)
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and milk over low heat.
Stir. Mix and add sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in all ingredients, except the Cool Whip.
Put the Cool Whip in last.
Place the salad in the refrigerator to chill.

title: brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, soda and oil.
Add this mixture to butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix milk and lime juice. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Pour into pie crust. Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Put in the microwave and cook for 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Take out and add soda gently stirring.
Pour on a cookie sheet.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cheese in bowl.
Add mixture to chicken.
Put about 2 tablespoons of mixture in tortilla and roll.
Add remaining mixture on top of rolled tortillas.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: beef steak pie with potato crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes. Coat with flour.
Melt shortening. Brown meat on all sides.
Add onions. Cook and stir until onions are tender. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons flour, salt, pepper, thyme and garlic salt.
Pour water over mixture. Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes until meat is tender.
Increase oven temperature to 450°. Arrange potatoes on meat. Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Beat and pour into greased baking pan.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Combine bacon and onion in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High (100%) until bacon is crisp and onion is tender, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Blend in flour. Stir in corn, milk, parsley, salt and pepper.
Microwave on High (100%) until slightly thickened and corn is tender, 7 to
12 minutes, stirring twice during cooking time.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: In a food processor, chop fine the cranberries and transfer to bowl.
In the processor, chop fine the oranges, including rind; add them to the cranberries along with the sugar and orange juice. Combine well.
Chill, covered, overnight and stir again before serving.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix well the margarine, condensed milk, sugar and vanilla. Add nuts. Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin wax in double boiler. Coat balls with this mixture and place on wax paper.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in a covered bowl in refrigerator. On the second day mix and return to refrigerator.
Third day do the same procedure.
Fourth day form into three rolls, place on broiler rack and bake 6 hours at 150° and 2 hours at 200°, turning every 2 hours.

title: frozen pumpkin squares
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl and mix the pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Scoop in with spoon the vanilla ice cream while mixing slowly.
When mixed well, add chopped pecans. Spread small amount of ice cream mixture over bottom of pan, then line bottom of pan with gingersnap cookies.
Cover with ice cream mixture.
Put another layer of gingersnap cookies.
Add remaining ice cream mixture over top.
Freeze until firm (about 5 hours or overnight).
Cut into squares; garnish with whipped topping and toasted pecan pieces.

title: all-bran refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl, mix shortening, water, sugar, All-Bran and salt. Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat eggs; stir into lukewarm ingredients.
Stir in yeast dissolved in water.
Add 3 cups whole wheat and 3 cups white flour, stirring as added.
Never use more than 7 cups.
Brush top with melted butter and cover tightly with wax paper.
Place in refrigerator for several hours or days.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until foams.
Add sugar, then beat until peaks foam.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Melt chocolate chips and add walnuts.
Fold into the above mixture.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend milk, lemon juice, lemon extract, and 2 eggs yolks.
Pour into crust.
Beat 3 egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff. Add sugar, then beat until stiff.
Spread on pie.
Seal edges, by dipping fingers into a little water and running over exposed pie crust to crystalize it.
Bake at 325 for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 1 hour, then refrigerate.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix.
Chill overnight.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix flour and baking powder in a bowl.
Add peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on warm hamburger rolls.

title: basil-tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring ocasionally.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: western lima bean bake
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Brown ground beef; add onion, bell pepper and tomato sauce.
Put beans in casserole dish and top with meat.
Can add thin layer of cornbread on top and you can add cheese before cornbread (optional).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Press 1/2 of the crushed crackers, chopped pecans and melted butter mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together softened ice cream, milk and instant pudding.
Pour over crust. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip, then sprinkle on remaining crumb mixture.
Refrigerate.
Can be made in any combination of flavors.

title: skewered grilled potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and water in 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Stir in potatoes; cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain, reserving salad dressing mixture.
Arrange potatoes on skewers.
Place on grill over hot coals.
Grill, covered, for 4 minutes.
Rotate skewers; brush with reserved salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling 4 minutes.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Place meat in pot.
Mix flour, tapioca and pepper; pour over meat.
Stir to coat meat with flour.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to mix well.
Cover; cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (or on high for 4 to 6 hours).
Stir stew thoroughly before serving.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Make cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cook and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook pudding as directed using evaporated milk (whole milk and liqueur of choice in the amounts listed). Chill until set.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in a 2-quart microwave dish. Microwave on 100% for 4 minutes; stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Will be light brown.
Add butter and vanilla. Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Add soda and stir gently.
Pour on greased baking sheet.
Let cool at room temperature.
Break into pieces (do not double recipe).

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until done.
Cut all vegetables up small in a large bowl.
When noodles are done, drain and mix with vegetables. Add salad dressing to vegetable mixture, then add salad seasoning.
Mix well.
Cool for about 6 hours and serve.

title: my mama's old fashioned dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Blend in butter, egg and milk to make a fairly stiff dough.
Roll on floured dough board, cut into squares and drop into boiling broth (in which chicken was cooked).
Cook 20 minutes and don't lift cover while cooking!

title: pizza sauce
directions: Blend in blender the hot peppers, garlic and onions.
Add to juice.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, then add 3 small cans of tomato paste. Cook until thickened.
Then fill hot jars and seal.

title: white sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Add ice before serving.

title: homemade beef jerky
directions: Slice meat lengthwise with the grain into 1/4-inch pieces. Combine remaining ingredients and mix with meat strips. Let stand 15 to 20 minutes. Drain and arrange in a single layer on a rack set in shallow baking pan. Bake in 150° oven or at lowest oven temperature for at least 12 hours. Store in airtight container. Better than store bought.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli, rice, soup, Velveeta and 1 cup onions; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and continue baking 5 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut angel flake pie
directions: Mix together and place in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
Test with toothpick to make sure center is done.

title: spectacular dessert
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° until brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Blend and spread over the crust the cream cheese, powdered sugar and nondairy topping.
Mix instant pudding and milk and spread over previous mixture.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread remaining topping on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream elderberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake for 40 minutes or more.
Test with knife.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in melted butter and egg and mix with milk.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: party mix
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix together remaining ingredients. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake on cookie sheets in 300° oven until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Store in airtight containers.

title: bierocks(hamburger and cabbage squares)
directions: In large pot, brown and crumble hamburger; add chopped onion and cook over low heat.
Add finely cut up cabbage and a little water.
Simmer with lid on for 45 minutes or longer; add seasoning.
Meanwhile, prepare hot roll mix according to directions on box and let rise (or make bread dough from your own recipe).
After risen, punch down; divide into half.
Roll half out into rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 6 squares.
Place in each square a large spoonful of cabbage mixture, cooled and drained.
Fold up corners to middle and squeeze dough together to seal.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
This recipe was given to me by my grandmother. These have been sold in grocery store deli in Russell, Kansas.

title: cayman islands raspberry bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour scalded cream over bread.
Blend sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon in blender.
Pour over bread and let soak 30 minutes.
Fold in raspberries and pour into buttered Pyrex dish or spring-form pan.
Bake in water bath for 1 hour until puffy and firm.

title: prune cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: onion "kuchen" bread
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Saute in butter in heavy skillet over low heat until transparent.
Spray round cake pan with Pam. Place biscuits in cake pan.
Spoon onion mixture on top of biscuits.
Combine egg, sour cream and salt.
Spoon over onion mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until topping is set.
Slice in wedges.
Serve warm.

title: better than ever cake
directions: Bake cake.
Punch holes while hot with end of wooden spoon. Boil pineapple and sugar.
Pour over cake.
Let cool.
Layer pudding.
Mix Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.
Spread over cake. Let set 24 hours.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Roll nuts, dates and candy in flour; add, along with coconut, to batter.
Bake in tube pan (greased and floured) at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: yugoslav vineyard vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil large shallow (3-quart) casserole.
In large bowl combine potatoes, eggplant, green pepper, zucchini, onion, carrots, parsley and peas.
Season with 1/3 cup olive oil, salt, Tabasco and black pepper.
Toss well. Place half of sliced tomatoes in bottom of prepared casserole. Cover with half of diced vegetables.
Sprinkle rice over vegetables.
Cover with remaining vegetables.
Cover with remaining sliced tomatoes.
Pour 3 tablespoons olive oil, vinegar and water.
Bake, covered, 1 3/4 to 2 hours until vegetables are tender.
Uncover.
Top with cheese.
Place under broiler 2 minutes until lightly browned.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Heat oil; add meat and brown.
Add onions and garlic.
Add other seasonings, tomato puree and water. Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add strips of green peppers and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve on noodles or rice.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together in electric mixer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Top with milk, mixed with Bisquick. Put in ungreased baking dish.
Bake 27 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and lemon extract.
Add 3 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix 1 cup flour with fruit.
Add fruit and nuts to other mixture.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 250°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease 9-inch pan.
Soften cheese at room temperature and beat in large bowl until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar and eggs; beat well after each one.
Fold in vanilla and sour cream.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Turn off oven and leave cake in oven for 1 hour. Chill after cake has cooled.

title: barbecue potato salad
directions: Marinate first 5 ingredients in dill pickle juice for at least 1 hour or overnight.
Chop potatoes into small squares and mix all ingredients with barbecue sauce and mayonnaise; then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: salt free lemon sauce
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine sugar and cornstarch. Slowly add the cold water and mix well.
Bring the mixture to a boil and add the butter, lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Continue to boil slowly until sauce becomes thick and opaque, about 10 minutes.
Delicious over plain cake or meringue cake.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix celery, mustard seed, salt, vinegar and sugar; heat until dissolved (do not boil).
Cool and pour over cucumbers.
Put in refrigerator.
Will keep for 4 months in refrigerator.

title: granola(kids recipe)
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Combine oil, honey and vanilla in a saucepan and warm.
Add these to the dry ingredients and stir until all the particles are coated.
(Hand mixing works well here).

Spread this mixture in a long, low pan or rimmed baking sheet that has been sprayed with vegetable shortening. Bake at 250° for an hour, turning with spatula every 15 minutes. When finished toasting, add raisins and toss.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: corn meal catfish
directions: Combine egg and water in pie plate until blended.
Spoon flour onto waxed paper; combine cornmeal, cheese, basil and salt on second piece of waxed paper.
Dredge fish in flour, dip in egg, then roll in corn meal mixture to coat.
Heat 2 teaspoons of oil in large skillet.
Place 2 fillets in skillet.
Cook first side 4 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Turn and cook other side 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Repeat with remaining fillets.

title: peaches and cream pie(this is scrumptious!)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Score vanilla beans and drop into vodka.
Tightly seal bottle and store in dark, cool, dry place, i.e., pantry.
Wait 6 months and voila, pure vanilla extract.

title: georgia torte
directions: Finely crush graham crackers.
Combine and mix with remaining ingredients.
Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Cook until tender and seal in sterilized jars. Do not over cook.

title: red hot cinnamon cider
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine juice or cider and candies. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until candies dissolve.
Serve hot or cold.
If desired, garnish with apple wedge or cinnamon stick stirrer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 oleo in casserole dish and put rest on top.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions.
Pour into prepared pans and bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Combine with brown sugar, ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire and bacon in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain beans, then stir beans into mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pueblo green chili stew
directions: In large Dutch oven or deep skillet with lid, lightly brown pork cubes in oil over medium-high heat.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot with fresh flour or corn tortillas.
Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave rhubarb sauce
directions: Cook rhubarb and water in microwave 5 minutes on High power. Add jello and sugar; cook 2 minutes longer. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter milkshake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into glasses and enjoy.

title: all fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl mix the sugar and fruit.
Pour butter into an 8 x 11-inch dish and put in oven to melt.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together and stir in milk to make batter.
Pour batter in melted butter.
Quickly spoon fruit and juices over batter.
Return to oven and bake about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix flour, leavenings, salt and spices in large bowl.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix molasses and 2 cups water.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, beating until smooth. Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven, about 35 minutes.
Serve hot with whipped cream.
Makes 24 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown sausage well and add the rest and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: italian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: margaret kalb's banana cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs just until combined.
Mix in bananas and buttermilk.
Sift together flour and soda and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into layer pans.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes, until cake tests done.

title: easy skillet goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Return it to skillet.
Add soups and sauce and stir until thickened.
Add corn, olives and cheese.
Stir and let simmer.
In the meantime, cook pasta.
Drain and add to meat and vegetable mixture.
Stir until blended. Sprinkle additional grated Cheddar cheese and let simmer until cheese is melted.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all together and put in graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: monastery pumpkin bread
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Break eggs into mixture.
Add the oil and water. Mix until all ingredients are combined.
Add pumpkin and mix. Don't overmix.
Pour batter into 2 pans (10 1/4 x 3 5/8 x 2 5/8). Sprinkle chopped walnuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hour. Turn out on rack to cool.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cut angel cake into bite-size pieces.
Place 1/2 of cake in bottom of rectangular glass dish.
Spread pie filling over cake. Put remaining 1/2 of cake pieces on top of filling.
Mix pudding and milk, then fold in sour cream.
Spread this over cake pieces and top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
A 9 x 13-inch pan is recommended.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook 1 hour the water, chicken breasts, 1 carrot, 1 onion, 1 teaspoon salt, basil, peppercorns, 1 rib of celery, garlic, thyme and parsley.
Skim foam.
Refrigerate chicken.
Skim fat.

title: citrus sage chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken breasts; pat dry and place in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour 1/2 of mixture over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Turn each piece and cover with remaining sauce; bake 15 to 20 minutes longer until done. Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles in leftover chicken broth.
When done, add chicken, Ro-Tel and soup.
Mix well.
Add cheese; simmer until melted.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Drain butter beans, reserving juice.
Arrange beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole in alternate layers with onion.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over layers.
Add reserved juice from beans and catsup to skillet in which pork chops were browned.
Arrange pork chops on top of beans in casserole.
Pour liquid over chops.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until chops are tender.
Serves 4.

title: good corn bread
directions: Beat the eggs and corn bread mix and the corn.
Brown sausage in skillet.
In a large skillet, pour half the corn bread mixture and put the sausage over it.
Place chopped peppers over sausage and the cheese over this.
Put the rest of the corn bread mixture on top, covering the sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Makes
(9 x 13-inch)
pan,
or
(8-inch)	layers. Grease and flour pans.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and stir until well mixed.
Batter will be
very liquid; pour into pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Drain whole corn.
Mix everything together, except cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with cheese and serve.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Melt cheese and tomatoes in microwave for 8 minutes.
Mix sausage and cheese sauce together.
Microwave for another 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: curried chicken balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in chicken, green onions and celery.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in nuts. Chill up to 2 days or freeze up to 1 month.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together powdered sugar and peanut butter until it is like crumbs.
Sprinkle in bottom of baked pie shell, reserving a small amount for top of pie.
Cook pudding as directed, adding lightly beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites to peaks.
Add sugar gradually.
Cover pie with meringue and sprinkle with reserved peanut mixture.
Bake at 425° until lightly brown.

title: minute chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in sauce for about an hour.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Coat Bundt pan with shortening and flour.
Add batter and topping alternately.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, bananas and eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased pan at 350°.

title: iowa potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup melted margarine in large bowl. Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine; sprinkle over top.

title: irma salad
directions: Mix fruit and chopped bananas with cottage cheese.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Put dry jello in and mix well.
Chill.

title: wiener chowder
directions: Saute frankfurters, green pepper and onion in margarine in 3-quart saucepan. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms and artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Place skin side up in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain artichokes, reserving liquid.
Cut artichokes in half.
Top chicken breasts with artichokes, mushrooms and green onions.
Pour reserved marinade and white wine over chicken.
Bake until chicken is cooked through, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix margarine and flour together.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 10x sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over first layer.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Spread over second layer.
Top with extra Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: quick and easy
directions: Tastes like you worked all day over a hot stove.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add softened cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish and salt.
Beat with beater until smooth. Add lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in cucumbers and onions.
Turn into a ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Mix and let sit a while.
Serve on romaine lettuce and shrimp.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and dice potatoes.
Fry bacon and drain on paper towels.
To bacon drippings, add onions and saut until tender. Add flour, sugar and celery seed.
Blend until smooth; add water and vinegar.
Simmer until thickened.
Fold in potatoes.
Crumble bacon and fold in.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring often.
Even better the next day!

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well. Dip your favorite fruit (strawberries, bananas, oranges, apples, etc.). Enjoy.

title: tangy yellow squash
directions: Combine all
ingredients and mix gently. Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: apricot pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell.
Place apricots in small saucepan and cover with Grand Marnier.
Place pan over medium heat, boil, cover, turn off heat and leave pan on burner.

title: briarpatch bean soup
directions: Melt butter and add crumbled sausage to brown.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add 1 can Great Northern beans.
Add 1/2 can water.
Cook for about one hour.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Put bottom crust in (9-inch) pie plate.
Break crackers coarsely into crust.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Cream butter with sugars.
Add eggs and beans.
Cream all together.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle pecans on top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll out in small balls and press down with fork.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the butter thoroughly.
Add grated cheese, sifted flour, salt and Tabasco sauce. Work up well and roll out very thin. Cut with a fancy cutter and top with pecan half.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: drop doughnut balls
directions: Mix sugar, milk and egg; add melted Crisco.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and spices, which have been sifted together, to the liquid mixture.
Combine the two mixtures lightly.
Drop from a teaspoon into deep Crisco, heated to 365° or until an inch cube of bread browns in 60 seconds.
Fry doughnut balls until brown and cooked in the center (about 4 minutes).
Drain on absorbent paper. Roll in powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pickled yellow squash
directions: Mix well.
Salt to taste.
Let stand for 1 hour and drain well.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour mixture over drained squash.
Bring back to boil for a short time (until peppers lose bright color).
Remove from heat and put in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 pints.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Pour contents of cans into pot.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until cranberry sauce is melted.
Gently put meatballs into sauce and simmer until meat is cooked.
Mushrooms (fresh or canned) may be added, if desired.
Good served over rice.

title: slow cooked beans
directions: Wash and drain dry beans.
Place in crock-pot.
Fill crock-pot 3/4 way with water.
Place hock in beans.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
When beans are almost done, season with salt and pepper. Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: rich rolls
directions: Combine scalded milk, margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/3 cup lukewarm water.
Stir and combine with cooled milk mixture.
Add
1/2 flour and the beaten eggs; beat well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead, about 10 minutes or until smooth and satiny.

title: texas hash
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring with a fork to break up the meat until lightly brown. Add other 9 ingredients, mixing well.
Turn into a greased casserole dish. Cover and bake in the oven at 375° for 45 minutes. Stir once or twice during cooking.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sutton gourmet marinara sauce
directions: In a hot pan, saute the garlic, bay leaf and tomatoes for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sugar, basil, salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute mushrooms.
Add to spaghetti; mix in almonds.
Make a sauce with butter, flour and chicken broth.
Warm whipping cream.
Add to sauce.
Cut up chicken in separate bowl. Pour half of sauce over chicken, other half over spaghetti.
Put spaghetti in greased casserole.
Pour chicken over and toss gently.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375° or until golden brown on top.

title: deer camp chili(makes a big pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a big pot; stir well.
Cover and simmer gently at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chili
directions: Combine all ingredients, except garlic, and cook until thick, about 2 hours.
Then add garlic.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix batter and put half in a greased and floured 9 X 13 pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread pie filling over top.
Then dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While warm drizzle with powdered sugar frosting, canned frosting, or cooked white icing.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Add onion, turnip and celery to meat.
Pan fry all ingredients in butter for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, thyme, sage to taste and 1/2 cup red wine.
Line a casserole dish with meat mixture.
Place mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: trash
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Put cereal into a large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over it. Stir around until cereal is all covered.
Place 1/2 box powdered sugar into a large brown paper bag.
Pour cereal mixture into bag and top with remaining 1/2 box of powdered sugar.
Roll bag in hands or shake until all covered.

title: purple passion
directions: Let this set up.

title: saganaki(flaming greek cheese)
directions: Cut cheese into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place cheese on ovenproof skillet.
Broil approximately 7 minutes.
The cheese should be just soft and the surface should bubble slightly.
Pour Metaxa over cheese and flame.
Squeeze lemon over cheese.
Serve immediately with Greek bread.

title: snowflake treat
directions: In a large bowl, beat 1 egg slightly.
Add sugar and salt. Add vanilla and 1 cup of milk or a little more.
Mix well, then stir in enough clean snow to make it thick.
Eat at once.

title: impossible zucchini pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together with a mixer.
Add eggs one at a time.
Blend well, then add Parmesan cheese and oil. Continue to blend well.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Pour mixture in.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture alternating with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool. Wrap and store overnight.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Saute onion in a little oil. Add ground beef, salt, pepper and oregano. Cook until beef is browned. Drain fat. Put meat in large mixing bowl. Add milk, catsup, bread crumbs and 3/4 of the cheese. Mix and put in baked pie shell. Mix Worcestershire sauce with remaining cheese and spread on top. Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scrumptious potatoes
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 stick margarine; add soup, sour cream and cheese until cheese is melted.
Break up potatoes into small pieces; place in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour mix over.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo; add 1 cup crushed corn flakes to this and spread over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together, blending well.
Add next 4 ingredients and blend well.
Bake in lightly greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Check with toothpick; might need another 10 minutes.
(Good for holiday.)

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chicken fat (or butter) in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch) or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Add sugar and acid in enamel boiler.
Add 2 quarts boiling water; dissolve quickly.
Add lemon and pineapple juices and 2 quarts water.
Add color.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook slowly. Pour in crust. Make meringue from the 3 egg whites.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and apples.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Cook a little longer than soft ball stage (when tested in cold water) the sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, corn syrup and milk.
Take off stove.
Add the butter or margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and walnuts.
Beat until it starts to get thick; pour in buttered pan (8 x 8-inch).
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Sift flour with salt; add 1/2 of it to creamed mixture.
Dissolve soda in the hot water.
Add to batter, then add remaining flour.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fancy pimento cheese
directions: Add cheese, onion and pimentos.
Mix with Miracle Whip and sweet pickle relish to taste.

title: cheesy broccoli and mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 18-inch pan. Whisk together soup, salad dressing and milk.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Do not cook completely.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken which has been put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain well.
Use a little margarine to saute onion.
Add all ingredients to cooked spinach. Put into fridge to cool.
Make into balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: spicy cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients well with blender.
Spread on tortillas. Roll tortillas and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into small wheels and serve with picante sauce.

title: sweet n' sour meat loaf
directions: Mix first six ingredients and shape into 4 individual loaves. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour off pan juices.
While loaves are baking, stir cornstarch and brown sugar together.
Add to tomato sauce, pineapple juice, soy sauce, and prepared mustard. Cook sauce stirring until thick.
Pour over meat loaves and bake, basting often, for 40 minutes longer.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Drain grease.
Add all sauces and Italian seasoning to taste.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Layer as follows:

sauce, 3 slices Mozzarella cheese and noodles; sauce, 8 slices American cheese and noodles; sauce, 3 slices Mozzarella cheese and noodles. Spread remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, then thin with small amounts of clam juice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corns, onion, bell pepper, eggs and cornbread mix. Pour into baking dish and cover with sour cream and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: old settler baked beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Fry bacon.
Chop.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add kidney beans, pork and beans, Ranch Style beans, chili beans and onion.
Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.
This makes a large recipe.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add chicken stock.
Add chopped broccoli and curry powder.
Cook until tender.
Make a cream base by blending together Ricotta cheese and low-fat milk.
Add to soup mix and blend.
Put finished soup in blender and process until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cherries, pineapple, milk, Cool Whip and nuts together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese, at room temperature, and blend well.
Add other ingredients and let set in refrigerator.

title: "po white trash" dip
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Stir in approximately 1/2 jar of Rosarita and mix well.
If more Rosarita is needed, add and mix well.
Add approximately 1/2 bottle of Bac N' Chips and stir well.
If more are needed, add and stir.
Best when refrigerated 24 hours.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown together the hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix all other ingredients with browned meat.
Stir well and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
This recipe is from my cousin, Vicki Bowen.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion, salt and pepper until browned. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover and set aside.
In separate pan, heat remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes and pour sauce into pie plate. Dip each tortilla into sauce, covering both sides.
Place into 12 x 9-inch baking dish and spoon 1/4 cup hamburger mix onto tortilla and roll around filling.
Pour remaining sauce and cheese over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 375° oven for 1 hour or until soft. Allow to cool. Cut a thin slice off top of each potato. Scoop out the pulp and mash it. Blend in milk, bacon, onion, chives, salt, pepper and 1 cup cheese. Spoon into potato shells. Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Place on baking sheet. Bake uncovered, at 375° for 25 - 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Par boil carrots. Brown beef, drain. In large pot, saute onions in margarine until onions are soft. Add beef and mix. Add remaining ingredients, Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 min.

title: beef veggie soup
directions: Cook and stir the beef and onion in a Dutch oven until beef is brown.
Stir in sauce mix, bay leaf, salt, pepper and tomatoes; heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Stir in noodles. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: white wine chicken
directions: Bone, skin and halve the two chicken breasts.
Sprinkle salt and nutmeg on both sides.
Brown in a skillet in two tablespoons butter.
Add two tablespoons minced onion, mushrooms and the white wine.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken to a warm serving platter.
Bring pan juices to a boil and cook, stirring juices until liquid is slightly reduced.
Stir in a mixture of one teaspoon cornstarch and two teaspoons of wine.
Cook, stirring mixture until thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken breasts when serving.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Mix together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in oil.
Add yeast water, then warm milk.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain, rinse and remove any bad beans. Put beans and next 7 ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours until done.
Serve in soup bowls with a large tablespoon of sour cream on top.
Garnish with hard-boiled egg or slice of lemon.
Serves 6.

title: cowboy taters
directions: Line pan or foil with bacon.
Layer potatoes and onion slices to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bacon slices. Enclose in foil and cook on grill or cover and put in 350° oven and cook until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hawaiian bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well mixed.
Add coconut, flour and salt; mix with fork until crumbly.
Press half of crumb mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread Pineapple Filling evenly over crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture and gently press down.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 1-inch bars.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater.
Put in uncooked pie shell and cook slowly, about one hour at 300°.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk/egg mixture.
Coat with mixed dry ingredients.
For crispier chicken, double dip chicken again.
Fry as usual.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then roll into balls and cover with chopped pecans.

title: golden cheese salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sour cream; beat until smooth.
Add pineapple; chill until partially set.
Fold in carrots and cheese; turn into a 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: nut cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix sweetener with orange juice.
Cream butter with orange juice mixture.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla, nuts and grated rind.
Form into roll; wrap in foil or wax paper.
Chill.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill casserole dish with sliced apples.
Cream butter and sugar.
Knead in flour and cinnamon (sort of crumbly).
Spread on top of apples.
Bake at 400° until bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes. Delicious with ice cream on top.

title: cheese-broccoli soup
directions: Cook broth, onion, potatoes, celery and broccoli for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, soup and water.
Heat again and add 1 pound Velveeta cheese.
This freezes well.

title: california lemonade
directions: Combine first three ingredients in 2-quart pitcher.
Serve over lemon slices.

title: leftover ham with noodles
directions: Brown ham in butter.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add milk to soup.
In casserole, alternate layers of ham/onion, noodles, cheese (cut into strips) and soup mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed turkey mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems on the mushrooms and chop.
Heat liquid Butter Buds in a skillet and cook the onion and ground turkey. Add the chopped mushroom stems and other ingredients.
Cook this mixture about 5 minutes.
Stuff this mixture into the mushroom caps and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Preheat broiler and place in oven for 2 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 20 stuffed mushrooms.
Per serving: .75 fat grams and 33 calories.

title: best ginger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill until dough can be handled.
Make into rolls about 1 1/2-inch diameter.
Cover with wax paper and put into refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven until brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes a big batch.
Recipe can be halved.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Line
a greased heatproof glass dish with quartered and floured tortillas.	Brown meat; add onion and seasonings; cook until
onions
are	tender.
Pour off most of the liquid if it has not cooked off.
Add undrained beans and mix well.	Remove from heat.
Spoon
over tortillas.
Cover with cheese.
Place soup
and tomatoes
in a blender.
Pour mixture over meat and beans.
Top with another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to
40 minutes.
Cut
in
squares	and
serve
hot with flour tortillas that
have	been warmed.
Better if assembled a day ahead, covered and refrigerated overnight and cooked the next day.

title: smothered pot roast
directions: Puncture meat with a fork on all sides.
Spread about 1/3 of cream soup in bottom of cooking bag.
Place roast on top of soup. Sprinkle soup mix evenly over meat.
Cover with remaining undiluted cream soup.
Gather end of bag.
Tie loosely leaving small space for steam to escape.
Plan cooking time at 25 to 30 minutes per pound.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) power for 1/2 the total time.
Turn roasting bag over.
Microwave for the remaining time.
Let roast stand in bag 20 to 30 minutes to complete tenderizing.
Serve meat thinly sliced with its sauce.

title: cheesy spinach bake
directions: Drain spinach, squeezing out excess liquid.
Combine all ingredients; pour into 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring oleo and water to a boil in saucepan.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Beat until mixture forms a ball; remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add pudding mix and milk; beat until thick and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Chill until serving time.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill cupcake cups half full.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt; stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture into each cupcake cup.
Bake as directed on cake mix package.

title: sfinges
directions: In a bowl, beat egg and sugar until light.
Add Ricotta cheese and blend well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture; alternate with milk.
Blend well.
Drop by tablespoon into deep, hot oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, until golden.
Turn one time.
Drain on paper towel. When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake cake until done.
Remove from oven; poke holes in cake while hot.
Pour milk and caramel over cake.
Let cool, then spread on cool whip and sprinkle with chips.

title: apples 'n cream coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and softened butter; mix well.
Add pudding, milk and egg; beat 2 minutes.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Pour in batter; arrange apple slices on top of batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and egg.
Beat smooth.
Spoon over batter to within 1-inch from edge.

title: beef burgundy barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Soak beef kabobs for 1 hour at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Grill or broil until desired doneness.

title: meat curry
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add onion, garlic, celery and apple.
Cook, stirring often, for about 5 minutes.
Blend flour, curry powder and mustard; sprinkle it over vegetables.
Stir.
Add bay leaf and chicken broth; rapidly stir with wire whisk.
When mixture has thickened, let simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir bottom often to prevent from sticking.
Add meat, milk and finely chopped chutney; simmer 4 to 5 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: party punch
directions: Put soda, pineapple and juice in punch bowl.
Add sherbet. Stir.

title: butterscotch filling
directions: Mix brown sugar, milk, salt, cornstarch and egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter when a little cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: d.q.  buster bars
directions: Smash Oreo cookies.
Mix 1 stick melted oleo with cookies. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put ice cream over cookies.
Put peanuts over ice cream.
Put fudge sauce over peanuts.
Put Cool Whip over sauce.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into small squares.

title: oven-fried ginger chicken
directions: Mix the flour, pepper, sesame seed, ginger and bran together in a small bowl.
Spray the chicken with the vegetable cooking spray and then dip in soy sauce.

Coat with the ginger mixture and place in a metal baking dish which has been coated with nonstick spray. Now lightly spray one more time with the vegetable cooking spray and drizzle the remaining soy sauce evenly over all chicken breasts.
Sprinkle bran crumbs on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 40 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 175 calories per serving.
Contains 23% fat.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together. Alternately add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla to creamed mixture. Mix well. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin-date muffins
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, pumpkin and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moist.
Fill greased muffin pans two-thirds full.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Fill each cone with cake mix.
Place cones on cookie sheet and put them in a preheated oven (follow cake mix directions for temperature and cooking time).
Remove from oven and cool.
Mix powdered sugar and milk; stir until smooth.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Frost the cupcakes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil hard 5 minutes the strawberries and sugar.
Add Epsom salts.
Boil 5 more minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cream oleo; add powdered sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time). Sift flour 2 more times and combine with sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 long loaf pan. Serve with fruit, if desired.

title: easy macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and heat through. Cook macaroni; drain.
Place macaroni in casserole dish and dot with cheddar cheese.
Put in spaghetti sauce and stir up.
Top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly and melted.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: quick saucy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, vegetables, poultry seasoning and garlic salt in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir baking mix and milk until blended.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 to 32 minutes or until crust is light golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza sheet and bake per package directions. Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar and spread on cooled cookie dough. Arrange fruit on top. Refrigerate.

title: ritzy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and diced cheese; mix well.
Add drained broccoli and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain well.
Combine soup, cheese, 1 cup crackers, mushrooms, milk, onion, ground pepper and pimiento. Stir in macaroni.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle on remaining 1/2 cup crackers.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with eggs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place roast in roasting pan.
Mix ketchup, beer, sugar, onion and sesame seed.
Pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Remove from oven and cool.
Remove all fat and any bones. Skim fat from sauce.
Shred beef; return to sauce.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Cook covered for 4 hours.
Serve on buns with onion and cheese, if desired.

title: jal.  cocktail squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle jal on well greased 9 x 9 inch baking dish. Cover with cheese then eggs. Bake 30 minutes or until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly butter two 11 x 17-inch baking sheets.
Sift the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl. Cream the butter and sugars together in another mixing bowl.
Stir in the milk, continuing to stir the egg, vanilla and milk until mixture is smooth.

Beat in the flour mixture a little at a time, then add the oatmeal, stirring until the mixture is well blended. Drop the batter by the spoonful onto the baking sheets, leaving space between for the cookies to expand.
Bake for 12 minutes, or until the cookies are lightly browned on top.

title: cinnamon pecan coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs, salt and yeast mixture in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Add 4 cups flour, beating at low speed and scraping bowl occasionally until mixture is smooth and elastic.
Stir remaining 3 1/2 cups flour to make a soft dough. Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise one hour.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl and set aside.
Punch dough down and shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls in melted butter, then in cinnamon mixture.

Layer half of balls in a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan, sprinkling with pecans after each layer. Repeat procedure with balls, butter, cinnamon mixture and pecans in another well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Cover both pans and chill dough 8 hours.
Pour topping glaze over dough.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Invert onto large serving platter.
Yields 2 (10-inch) coffee cakes.

title: barb's creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cover chicken with water; add salt and bouillon cubes.	Cook until chicken is tender (45 minutes to an hour).
Remove chicken and set aside to cool.
Strain out 2 cups of broth into a large cooker.
Pour in milk.
Mix flour or cornstarch with 1/4 cup of cooled broth.
Bring milk mixture to boil and slowly stir in the cornstarch mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain and add to broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to noodle mixture and cook a few minutes more.

title: zola's pecan sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Sift salt and baking powder with flour; add vanilla and pecans.
Grease pan and dust with flour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Ice when cool with butter or caramel icing, then cut in sticks or squares.
Cool before removing from pan, about 20 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into large plastic bag with powdered sugar and shake until well mixed.
Pour out on cookie sheet and cool.
A good snack!

title: adeline's zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce and mix together in large pot.
Place mixture into greased 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and put into a large bowl.
In saucepan, mix the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Heat to dissolve sugar, then pour over vegetables and toss.
Add sliced onion and bell pepper.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Open can of salmon and drain liquid into bowl.
Toast the bread; crumble into liquid.
Stir so all liquid is soaked up.
Add the egg and the salmon.
Flake salmon with fork and mix all ingredients.
Put the oil in a pan.
Shape salmon mixture into patties (about a heaping tablespoonful).
You can just put in pan and press with spoon to flatten a bit.
Fry in medium heat until brown; turn and brown other side.
Add more oil if needed.
Serve with baked potato or macaroni and cheese and salad or fresh sliced tomato.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Place crushed cookies in 9 x 9-inch pan and save some for top. Add ice cream; top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remainder of crushed cookies and nuts over top.
Freeze 3 hours before serving.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook shells and brown ground beef. Combine salsa, water and tomato sauce.
Of that, stir 1/2 cup into ground beef along with green chilies, 1 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Mix well.
Of the remaining sauce, pour 1/2 on the bottom of baking dish.
Stuff cooked shells with the ground beef mixture. Arrange shells in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: crab louis
directions: Drain
crabmeat
and
remove
cartilage; chill.
Prepare Louis Dressing.
Arrange crabmeat, tomatoes, eggs and olives on greens. Pour Louis Dressing over salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf cups
directions: In a large bowl combine the first eight ingredients. Add beef, mix well. Press into 12 foil lined or greased muffin cups. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until the meat is no longer pink. Drain before serving. Drizzle with ketchup if desired.

title: shrimp, crab and corn soup
directions: Saute bacon and onion; stir in corn and margarine.
Cook until margarine melts.
Add flour and stir well.
Add stocks, oregano, pimento and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Add shrimp, crab and half and half.
Season with hot pepper sauce. Bring to boil.
Adjust seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: brunch sandwich
directions: Cut crust from bread and butter the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Lay slices of bread in pan; over this, lay ham and cheese.
Top with second slice of bread.

title: red pepper lasagna
directions: Halve red peppers; remove stems, seeds and membranes.
Place peppers, cut side down, on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake in a 425 degree oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until skin is bubbly and blackened.
Wrap peppers in the foil and let stand 20 to 30 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
Peel skin from peppers and cut into thin strips.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage; cook until cabbage is almost soft.
Combine meat, rice, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Remove individual cabbage leaves.
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons of meat mixture at the top of the leaf.
Roll leaf up, tucking in sides.
Place cabbage rolls in a roasting dish.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook in a 350° oven for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
You may wish to add more tomatoes or a little water if needed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain. Add all together. Top with crushed Ritz crackers or bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers very thin.
Place in bowl.
Sprinkle very generously with salt.
Cover and refrigerate 6 to 12 hours. Squeeze handfuls to get rid of excess liquids.
In bowl, mix all other ingredients.
Add squeezed cucumbers and mix.

title: tomato-shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with soup.
Blend well.
Add seasonings, blending thoroughly.
Add shrimp.
Serve with dip chips or crackers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs 3 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle walnuts onto dough.
Bake 15 minutes.
Turn out onto a towel; let cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion together.
Add tomato sauce, water and spices.
Mix beef and macaroni together in 10 x 15-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place pepperoni over cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a sauce pan, cook (uncovered) broccoli and onions in chicken broth for 8 to 10 minutes. In another sauce pan, melt butter and add flour gradually. Add milk and stir with a wire whisk. Add broccoli and broth mixture to cheese sauce. Simmer on low for 5 to 10 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pat's pie
directions: Flour and grease 9-inch glass pan.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Slice onion thin and chop green pepper small.

title: kahlua toffee trifle
directions: Bake cake according to box directions in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Cut in half when cooled and crumble one of the halves in the bottom of a large glass bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the Kahlua over the crumbled cake.
Spread 1/2 of the chilled pudding over cake. Top the cake with 8 ounces of the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle 3 crushed Heath bars over Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers.
Keep chilled. Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow dish or Baggie.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Marinate in refrigerator 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Grill to desired doneness 5 to 10 minutes each side.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Cream flour
with
oleo and chopped nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at
350° for 25 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and half
of
the
Cool
Whip.	Spread	on cooled crust.
Beat pudding with milk and lemon juice.
Spread on first layer.
Top
with
remaining	Cool
Whip and sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate or freeze for later use.

title: pineapple cheese mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Put on medium heat; cook.
Add heated pineapple and stir to dissolve the gleatin. Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in cheese and cream.
Pour into a mold.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Cook peas.
Brown sausage and onion; drain fat off.
Drain peas.
Stir all other ingredients into peas.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon-cheese pie
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine eggs and milk; beat well.
Add to dry ingredients and mix only until flour is moistened.
Roll out 2/3 of dough to fit 9-inch pie pan.
Drain salmon (or mackerel); flake into bowl, removing skin and bones.
Add onion and salmon juice.
Turn into pie pan.
Cover with cheese.
Roll out remaining dough; place on top of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, then add crab, cheese and onion. Put in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can also use tuna, chopped ham, cubed cooked chicken or shrimp.

title: chicken breasts with rice
directions: Put rice and water in baking dish.
In medium bowl, mix together cream of celery, sour cream, salt, pepper, garlic powder and minced onion to taste.
Spread over rice and water.
Top with chicken breasts with a thin slice of Velveeta cheese under each breast.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, peanut butter and milk to a boil.
Then add the vanilla and the oats.
Shape into cookies.

title: cream white icing
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add flour, one tablespoon at a time. Add milk, then add vanilla with pinch of salt.
Beat until fluffy, then beat for about 20 minutes.
The longer you beat it, it will spread better.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well all together.
Bake at 350° until center is done.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and water.
Shape into balls in the size of walnuts.
Put into a casserole dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. If desired, all beef may be used.

title: orange "torch" whip mold
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Place mandarin oranges on top.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Prepare 1 box Duncan Hines yellow cake mix according to package directions.

title: dump it cake
directions: Butter a 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dump pineapple and cherries into pan.
Dump cake mix on top of mixture.
Press down.
Chop walnuts.
Sprinkle on top.
Slice 1 cube margarine and lay evenly over cake mix.
Put in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Mix bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, then beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Sear pork chops 2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour water into skillet. Scatter onions over chops.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes turning chops over once during cooking.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking covered for 20 minutes or until pork chops are tender.

title: vegetable fettucini
directions: Saute broccoli, zucchini, green pepper, onion and basil in oleo until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Then add mushrooms and tomatoes, diced.
Simmer about 5 minutes longer.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon and combine all ingredients.
Place in well-greased 6-cup muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Dredge meat in mixture of flour,
salt,
paprika
and
pepper.
Brown well in shortening. Add onion, 57 sauce and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover.
