Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Thicken liquid with a flour and water mixture.

title: mushroom curry
directions: Rinse the mushrooms in cold water; drain well.
Cut in halves or if large in quarters.
Peel the potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan and fry onions, herbs and ginger for about 5 minutes. Add the salt, turmeric and chili powder.
Fry for 2 more minutes, then add sliced tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly and cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
If you want liquid, cook covered; if not, cook uncovered.
Add the lemon juice and curry powder and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients together for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: banana muffins(sugar-free)
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients well. Divide in muffin pan with 12 cups.
Bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes. They should spring back when touched and are slightly brown on top.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips. Put into casserole and bake about 15 minutes at 425°. Place the crushed potato chips on top of casserole before baking or just before serving.
Serves about 4 or 5 women.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crab-asparagus casserole
directions: Note:
I use imitation crab; very good!

title: chicken chowder
directions: Barely cover chicken with water; add salt and onion.
Bring to a boil and then simmer until chicken is done.
Remove meat from bone and cut into serving pieces.
Extend broth with Swanson's chicken broth to equal 4 cups.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Blend milk and flour until smooth. Stir into broth with butter and cheese.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add wine and season to taste.

title: memaw's rich cinnamon cookies
directions: Preheat oven.
Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add sifted ingredients; add beaten eggs.
Mold with cookie press or drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth; cook and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat and set aside.
In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: fudge squares
directions: For fudge squares, melt butter and add cocoa.
Then mix in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in flour and vanilla.
Add nuts and bake for 30 or 35 minutes at 325°.

title: best of all fruitcakes(really, it will make your grandmother jealous!)
directions: Read completely before starting:

title: ginger pear jam
directions: Chop pears; add juice, finely chopped ginger, juice of lemon and grated rind, sugar and molasses.
Cook slowly in a heavy saucepan for 10 minutes.
Add pectin and boil rapidly 5 minutes. Pack in hot jars and seal at once.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken with stalk of celery and onion in pot of salted water.
Debone; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Crush crackers.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer chicken, soup, then crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top and then dribble margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add the buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
You will know when you have used enough flour when the ingredients are firm. Roll out on flour and cut the size you like (medium size cookie cutter).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: meatball and rice casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into 18 meatballs (1 1/2-inch diameter).
Brown in oil.
Drain.
Place in greased baking dish. Mix together rice, celery, green pepper, soup and water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Spread bread crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly with dry ingredients. Peel apple; cut into bite size pieces.
Add to bread.
Measure milk into 1-quart measuring cup.
Add butter.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir eggs into milk.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and sugar to taste.
Taste for flavor of eggnog.
Pour mixture over bread and apples.
Mix up and microwave for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juices from all fruit and keep it!!
Add remaining water until it adds up to 1 1/2 cups.
Boil that and add to jello.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved.
Pour in fruit and sherbet.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Cake:
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans.
Prepare batter as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly between pans.
Bake and cool as directed on package.

title: plain cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and add the sugar gradually, stirring until well mixed.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add the milk alternately with the flour (which has been sifted before measuring and sifted again with the baking powder) and salt.
When the batter is smooth, add the vanilla.
Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 15 (2 3/4-inch) cupcakes.
Ice if you want to, but these are delicious uniced.

title: crispy corn flake cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cornflakes.
Add cornflakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and soak them in cold water. Grate them and pour off the liquid.
Add the grated onion, salt and pepper.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to the potatoes.
Add well beaten eggs. Drop by spoonfuls on a hot, well greased skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use on seafood.

title: chicken and beef roll-ups
directions: Line baking dish with beef.
Around each piece of boneless, skinless chicken, wrap a slice of breakfast bacon.
Put this in baking dish over beef.
Mix soup, water and sour cream.
Pour this mixture over the chicken and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: crescent pecan pie bars
directions: Lightly grease (not oil) a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Separate crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of pan to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Combine egg, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes, until brown. Cool; cut into bars.

title: golden eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1-quart casserole. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: golden apple fritters
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Combine eggs, milk and oil. Core and finely chop the apples to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add apples and raisins to egg-milk mixture. Add flour mixture; mix thoroughly. Drop batter by tablespoon into oil heated to 375°.
Deep fry and turn until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Serve hot with syrup and/or powdered sugar. Makes about 16 fritters.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Add butter (melted).
Mix well.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda, then add this mixture to preceding mixture.
Add (slowly) oatmeal, mixing well. Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Form balls in hands, about walnut size.
Place on cookie sheet so can spread.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cook sugar, vanilla, cocoa, butter and milk over medium heat, 2 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats. Spoon out on wax paper.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in butter.
Add broth and broccoli; cook, stirring, until heated through and smooth.
Add milk and cook until just scalded (do not boil).
Serve hot.

title: frijoles
directions: Soak ingredients over 12 hours in refrigerator.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer, stirring from time to time, for about 1 1/2 hours, until tender.
To serve, top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: lentil soup
directions: Spray a heavy, 4-quart skillet with nonstick vegetable spray. Brown lightly onions, potato, mushrooms, garlic, carrot and celery.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, partially covered, until lentils are soft (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Add more water, if needed, during cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg delight
directions: Combine cheese, milk, flour, cottage cheese, eggs and 1/2 of the melted butter.
Spread remaining 1/2 of the melted butter in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture into the dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden and set.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 inch water until tender.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
(Do not grease.)
Beat soup and milk together, pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix with firm butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until light brown, about 20 minutes in 400° oven.
You can add onions, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 2-quart casserole dish. Place potatoes, onion and ham in casserole dish. In saucepan, mix milk, salt, butter, pepper and flour. Cook on medium heat until smooth and bubbly. Add cream of mushroom soup. May need to add a little more milk. Pour over the potatoes. Dot potatoes with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until tender.

title: strawberries 'n cream cake
directions: Mix berries with glaze and set aside.
Pinch cake into small pieces and set aside.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, milk and sugar. In large bowl, layer the cake, then Cool Whip and berries.
Repeat layers, cover and chill overnight.

title: shrimp dijon
directions: Prepare marinade; cook shrimp.
Mix and chill 24 hours ahead. Serve in a shallow pan.

title: huntington chicken
directions: Stew chicken; remove from bone in large pieces.
Thicken broth with flour and fat.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine chicken, macaroni, cheese, broth and soup.
Put into greased casserole and cover with crumbs which have been toasted in butter and a little cream.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes and add the eggs, flour, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
In a skillet, heat the oil and butter until hot.
Shape the mixture into patties and fry in the hot oil. Serves 6.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together and bake in three layers at 350° until done.

title: mexican stuffed zucchini for large squash
directions: Slice squash lengthwise.
Scoop out center.
Add enchilada sauce, combined with the water in large shallow pan.
Skin side down, cover and steam at 325° for 30 minutes.
Saute bacon 4 to 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Cook until onions are clear.
Remove from heat; add corn, olives, rice, chili salsa or other Mexican sauce.
Add eggs, salt and pepper; mix together.
Scoop into squash; top with cheese.
Cover.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.
Stir in cubed bread in butter until slightly browned and toasted.
Set aside. Mix rest of ingredients in bowl.
Add bread and mix well.
Put in a 2-quart buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, 1 cup orange juice, oil and orange peel.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Pour into pan.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add half and half until slightly thickened.
Remove; add cream cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in chicken and next five ingredients.
Fold noodles into mixture and place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs; coat with cooking spray and cover.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 additional minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour, salt and baking soda together and add to creamed mixture.
Mix and then add nuts or dates and bananas.
Mix well and then pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Layer bottom of pan with 1/2 package hash browns.
Place bread on top.
Next ham chunks.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over layers.
Sprinkle remainder of hash browns and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow to set for 10 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix the ingredients together in the order given.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: squash-carrot casserole
directions: Cook the squash, onions and carrots in boiling water until tender, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients except butter and stuffing mix and mix well.
Mix butter with stuffing mix and place half the mixture in a greased casserole.
Add squash mixture and place remaining stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: benny's juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; divide the mix into 6 sections, forming hamburger patty.
Barbecue or broil the patties for 6 to 8 minutes on each side, brushing with barbecue sauce. Add cheese, if you like, when the second side is nearly cooked. Serve on a hamburger bun with toppings.

title: red eye gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a very large bowl.
Add the steaks and turn gently to coat both sides of the meat with the marinade liquid.
Refrigerate and let marinate overnight.
Ready to grill or broil.
If cooking the steaks outside on a grill, baste your meats with this mixture while steaks are cooking.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter at room temperature. Add sugar.
Cream together well.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and
nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and flour until fluffy.
Blend in Karo syrup, then one egg at a time.
Blend in salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in a 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then 1 hour at 325°.

title: peanut butter puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl. Stir gently until coated.
Place confectioners sugar in a large paper bag. Add cereal mix to bag about 1/4 at a time. Shake until coated.
Spread on tray to cool and dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet.
Put on layer of ham and a layer of cheese.
Fold it over and pin with toothpick.
Dip the meat in egg, beaten, and then slip it into bread crumbs.
Fry on medium heat until done.

title: all-vegetable chili
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook celery, onion and green pepper until tender, stirring mixture occasionally.
Turn heat to high.

Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, undrained kidney and pinto beans, green chilies, zucchini, carrot, oregano, salt and crushed red pepper until boiling. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, ladle chili into bowls and top with cheese.
Makes 5 main dish servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal chews
directions: Melt chocolate chips and stir in shortening and salt.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Add melted chocolate mixture.
Add oats and vanilla. Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Watch carefully not to overbake.
These are a chocolate lover's delight.

title: butterscotch dip
directions: Place in mixing bowl and heat in microwave for 1 minute. Remove and stir.
Return to microwave for 1 minute more.
Continue until all morsels are melted.
Serve warm with apples.
Granny Smith are best.

title: two lemon pies
directions: Mix together the lemon juice, milk and pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours.
Remove; fold in Cool Whip and place in pie shells.
Place in freezer.
Remove 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix the bread mix, eggs, milk, peppers and pimento.
Layer half of the sausage, corn, cornbread mixture and cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Top with the melted margarine.
Bake at 400° until light brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti as directed on box and drain.
Saute all vegetables, mushrooms, parsley, olives, onion and green pepper until crisp, but not tender.
Drain and set aside.
Cook meat. When done, drain meat and mix in veggies and spaghetti sauce in a bowl big enough to stir the mixture in.
Mix the sauce mixture with the spaghetti.

title: less work mashed potatoes
directions: Scrub gently under water to remove dirt and dig out any bad spots, but do not peel.
Cut potatoes in half and boil until tender.
Drain well and let sit for 5 minutes, covered.
Add 4 to 5 tablespoons of butter or margarine.
Add Lawry's salt to taste and warm milk to the desired consistency.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
A mixer can be used until adding flour, then it will be too thick for mixer.
Mix by hand the rest of the way.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges barely begin to brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add berries, eggs and oil.
Mix by hand until blended.
Add food coloring.
Pour into two lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and beet water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets to hot sauce and let stand at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, bring to boiling point and add butter.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and put in a graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and shortening until mixture becomes crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Mix molasses, baking soda and water until soda is entirely dissolved and mixture becomes slightly foamy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle reserved 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until firm.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together sugar, stick and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or 2 layers in oblong pans.

title: tamale pie
directions: Put this in layers as written.
Top with corn chips and Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine chicken, onion, olive oil, lime juice, peppers, garlic and salsa in sealed plastic bag.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.
Grill or broil chicken and vegetables from 4 to 5-inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes per side while bringing marinade to a boil.
Cut chicken and vegetables into thin strips. Divide among tortillas and drizzle with marinade.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Roll up.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine ingredients and pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, stirring halfway through.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well and add just enough milk to give a soft consistency. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chewy candy bars
directions: Bottom Layer:
Beat together the butter, sugar, egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla in a bowl.
Add flour, soda, salt and oats; mix well.
Pack into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Beat milk, cream cheese and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla together well.
Reserve 3 tablespoons for icing.
Spread remainder over bottom layer. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until set.
Frost while hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to zucchini mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans or 4 small pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with herbed tomatoes and cheese
directions: Cook spaghetti according to the directions on the package.
In the last few minutes of the cooking of the spaghetti, place a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat; add the olive oil and stir until oil is hot.
Cook the garlic in the oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and salt; heat through, stirring occasionally. Drain spaghetti.
Return spaghetti to pot; add tomato mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: chinese eggs
directions: Melt butter and soy sauce in a skillet. Add eggs and cook for 5 minutes, basting and turning eggs until the eggs become dark. Brown. Slice eggs and place on serving plate. Drizzle with sesame oil and sprinkle with chopped green onion. Can be served warm or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs and pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top and bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, milk, Crisco and cocoa.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop from spoon onto a wax paper.
Let set until hard.

title: beef diablo
directions: Trim all excess fat from roast.
Place potatoes in bottom of crock-pot.
Lay sliced onions over potatoes.
Place roast over potatoes.
Pour 1/2 cup water over roast.
Make paste of remaining ingredients and spread paste over roast.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
(I usually put this on to cook in morning.
While I'm at work, my dinner is cooking.)
Make a nice tossed salad, rolls and tea.
You have a lovely dinner.

title: strawberry jello salad(serves 16 to 20)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add the strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and let set up.
Then spread a thin layer of sour cream and pour the remaining strawberry mixture on top.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: cheese fondue
directions: In a greased casserole dish, put alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Combine eggs and add milk and salt.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Pour melted butter over top of entire mixture.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a shallow pan of water at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: potato chili-cheese soup
directions: Clean potatoes; chop bite size and put in boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile, saute green peppers, onions, salt, cumin, basil, garlic and pepper in butter and olive oil.
Add green chiles.
Puree 1/2 of potatoes in processor and 1/2 saute in mixer.
Add sour cream, milk, cheese, scallions and remainder of potatoes.
This is a thick, milky soup.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 x 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside. Combine next 5 ingredients. Dip chicken into batter and fry in hot oil (325°) until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: cottage cheese-nut croquettes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Divide and shape into 10 equal croquettes.
Lightly beat egg and milk.
Dip croquettes into this mixture, then roll into corn flake crumbs. Bake on greased cookie sheet 25 minutes at 350°.
Good served with any tomato sauce.
Makes 10 croquettes, 100 calories per serving.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind 1 pound bologna or ham.
Add ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Place butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and place in oven to melt. Remove pan from oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter and press down with fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs, then add layer of chips and pecans.
Drizzle surface with condensed milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pepper and herb mini focaccia
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease two cookie sheets.
Remove dough from can; separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks. Place coils on greased cookie sheets.
Press each roll into a 5-inch circle.
Brush each with olive oil; sprinkle each evenly with bell peppers, basil and oregano.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Set aside.
Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Add beef over high heat until brown.
If not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up; add vegetables.
Stir until vegetables are crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine lime juice and condensed milk and whip until thick. Add Cool Whip and continue beating until well mixed.
Put in baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Top with more Cool Whip.
Mmm!

title: rib sauce
directions: Let ribs marinate in sauce for a couple of hours to overnight.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: rotel
directions: Cook all together 30 minutes.
Fill jars; seal and put in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown chuck and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spray baking dish with Pam and layer 1/2 of sauce, dry noodles and cheese mixture; repeat with other half.
Cook for 45 minutes covered.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more.

title: spanish style eggplant
directions: Saute eggplant, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in spray-coated or non-stick fry pan.
Add water as needed, a tablespoon at a time, to prevent sticking.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until eggplant is tender and flavors are blended.
This may be served as a vegetable or as a topping over brown rice.
Yields seven 1-cup servings.

title: grilled fish
directions: Put aluminum foil on grill.
Punch holes in foil.
Spray foil with Pam cooking spray.
Place fish, skin side down.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Squeeze lemon juice on fillet.
Cook on grill at medium temperature for 15 to 20 minutes or until flaky.
Top with Molly McButter flakes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients by layer in order listed.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then cut into small squares.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill for a short time.
Make into small balls and bake on an ungreased sheet at 325° for 15 minutes.
Use a spoon to thumbprint.
Add powdered sugar icing when cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: brown sugar shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter with sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Fashion into balls the size of walnuts. Flatten with rolling pin to 1/3-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 4 dozen if a cookie stamp is used or 3 dozen if cut out with cookie cutter.

title: welsh tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Cut in butter. Add sugar and currants.
Make a stiff dough with egg and a little water or milk.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut into 2-inch circles.
Bake on griddle or in electric fry pan set at 340°, turning cakes once.
When cool, sprinkle with fine granulated sugar.
Serve warm or cold with marmalade.

title: scalloped cabbage with cheese
directions: Cook cabbage.
Put cabbage into a greased baking dish; add a layer of cheese, layer of white sauce.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used.
Cover top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: fondant for chocolates
directions: Mix with hands until well blended.
Separate into dishes and tint with food coloring and flavoring to taste.
Roll into balls or patties and dip in chocolate.
Place on wax paper and cool or refrigerate.

title: yummy zonkers
directions: Pop popcorn.
Add remaining ingredients in a saucepan, except soda; bring to a hard boil, fast.
Add the soda.
Mix well and pour over popcorn.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Cut breasts into strips.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Dip into egg mixture.
Roll in flour.
Deep fry.

title: pink lady
directions: Place sugar in pitcher. Add cranberry juice slowly;

stir until sugar is dissolved. Add pineapple juice; chill thoroughly. Add ginger ale; pour into serving glasses. Add 1 serving spoon of ice milk to each glass; stir until foamy. Serve immediately. Makes about 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer chicken in water for 45 minutes or until tender.
Drain and reserve 2 1/2 cups broth.
Set chicken aside.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and add next 7 ingredients to broth and cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine milk and cornstarch.
Add to vegetable mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken, skinned and deboned, to vegetable mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased baking dish.
Roll biscuits thinly and arrange on top.
Use canned biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, thoroughly and form into balls.
Mix tomato soup and 1 soup can of water, pour over meat balls in a quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1-1/2 hours at 325 degrees.

title: fudge candy
directions: Boil sugar, cream, shortening and salt until it is a soft ball.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips, vanilla and nutmeats.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.

title: cauliflower and ham chowder
directions: In a large uncovered saucepan, cook celery and cauliflower in chicken broth until almost tender (about 10 minutes). Set aside. In a mixing bowl, gradually stir milk into undiluted potato soup. Blend water, cornstarch and pepper. Stir into soup mixture; pour over cauliflower mixture in the saucepan. Stir in ham and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes. Just before serving, stir in cheese.

title: roman grilled chicken
directions: Pour a little dressing in a baking pan.
Put chicken in (enough to cover bottom of pan).
Pour rest of dressing over chicken. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: stuffed dates
directions: In a small bowl, combine peanut butter and 1 teaspoon orange peel; spoon 1/8 of the mixture into each date.
Sift an equal amount of sugar over each filled date, then sprinkle each with 1/8 of the remaining orange peel.

title: 30 minute fried rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in heavy skillet with tight fitting lid. Remove bacon and all but 1/3 cup drippings.
Add rice and brown; add onion, cook 1 minute more.
Add other ingredients along with crumbled bacon.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Makes large amount and freezes well.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Take out 1 cup sugar mixture and stir into stiffly beaten egg whites; set aside.
Return remaining syrup mixture to heat and cook to hard ball stage; pour slowly into egg mixture, beating continuously.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat until it starts to harden.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan to cool.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: scalloped cod
directions: Preheat to 375°.
Melt butter in saucepan, slowly add flour until blended.

Stir in milk, add lemon juice, salt and pepper. In greased baking dish, lay out cod fillets. Sprinkle 1\2 of the bread crumbs, and all of the celery over the cod. Pour sauce evenly over cod. Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs over all.
Dot with butter and grated parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 min. or until bread crumbs are golden brown.

title: louisiana hush puppies
directions: Cook cornmeal and water over medium heat until all water is absorbed. Remove from heat and stir in milk, oil and grated onion. Gradually add beaten eggs, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Stir to mix well. Refrigerate about 1 hour; remove and drop by teaspoon into hot grease. Cook over medium heat until golden brown. Yields 18 to 24.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water in a saucepan just until tender; drain. Layer carrots, onion rings and green pepper rings in a bowl. Combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt and pepper in a saucepan; mix well. Bring to a boil. Pour over layers. Marinate, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Yield: 12 servings.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, milk, pineapple and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake immediately after mixing.

title: southwestern corn bake
directions: Combine everything except cheese and chilies.
Pour 1/2 of corn mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread chilies on mixture. Cover with cheese.
Pour remaining corn mixture on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: baked green rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions; set aside.
Lightly grease 9 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine rice, cheese, chilies, onions and parsley; mix.
Melt margarine.
Beat eggs and combine with milk and margarine.
Mix with rice mixture.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs and butter in a 9-inch pie pan.
Press firmly over bottom and side.
Chill.
Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and blend.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Turn into crust; refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate.
When cold, cut in pinwheels.
Serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Soften sherbet; add 7-Up and blend until slushy.
Needs no additional ice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend sugar, peanut butter, and margarine; add vanilla and salt.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill for a few hours or overnight.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and make 1 large or 2 medium loaves.

title: chocolate orange bars
directions: Blend together margarine, flour and sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan; press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs well.
Blend in brown sugar.
Stir in coconut, nuts, vanilla and 3/4 of chocolate chips.
Add salt and flour.
Spread evenly over baked layer.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie crust.
Dot with butter. Cover with crust.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Fry out sausage and pour off fat.
Drain. Cook onions and peppers in same pan.
Mix sauces and everything together.

title: triple layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted margarine. Top evenly with coconut, then sweetened milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt chips with peanut butter. Spread evenly over hot coconut layer. Garnish as desired. Store in loosely covered dish at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat in saucepan or kettle for 1 minute. Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls, 4 or 5 at a time, into hot oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once or until golden brown.
They brown very quickly.
Drain oil out by paper towel.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: super easy dip
directions: Mix together.
Really good served with Ritz crackers.

title: angel pudding dessert
directions: Cut cake into 1-inch cubes.
Place half of cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (glass).
Combine milk and pudding mix; beat until smooth and slightly thickened.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour half of pudding mixture over cake.
Spoon half of filling next.
Repeat layers.
Smooth top with spatula.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Very good!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the onion with the margarine.
Add soup.
Pour this mixture over broccoli in a casserole dish.
Add shredded cheese on top of the broccoli.
Put bread crumbs on top of mixture after moistening it with water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate butterfinger ice cream(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: To make 2 gallons, use 12 Butterfingers, but triple other ingredients.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra into hot jars.
Add dill, onions, red pepper (to taste) and garlic on top of okra.
Combine water, vinegar and salt; heat to boiling.
Pour over okra and seal at once.
Let stand 3 to 4 weeks.

title: corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, add onions and pepper; cook until tender.
In processor, blend 1 cup milk, flour and 1 cup corn on low speed until smooth.
Stir corn mixture with the remaining cup of corn and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: cheesy salmon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Place shredded potatoes in pie plate for crust.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over potato crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until pie is set and top is golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Combine soups, broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add chicken; mix well.
Butter 9 x 13-inch dish. Layer chips and chicken mixture and layer of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple orange salad
directions: Put pineapple with juice in large sauce pan, bring to boil. Add Jello, stir to dissolve. Cool slightly.
Add the buttermilk, stir. Pour into serving dish.
Decorate with dollups of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, milk, dates and nuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 12 x 3-inch baking pan.
Pour brown sugar over (don't mix together).
Bake in slow oven for 40 minutes (300° or less).
Does tend to boil over so larger container would be okay.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples. Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm and, if desired, with cream or ice cream. Makes 6 servings with 295 calories per serving.

title: never fail pie crust(two double crusts)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until flour is moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be re-rolled without toughening.
It also keeps in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown and crumble sausage. Drain and set aside.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift the first four ingredients. Blend the remaining ingredients and add to the flour mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cover the last 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cut up potatoes.
Boil and make into mashed potatoes.
While potatoes are cooking, brown ground beef and drain grease.
Mix ground beef, can of green beans (drained) and mushroom soup.
Put this mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Spread your mashed potatoes on top.
Cook in 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes.

title: frozen chocolate charlotte
directions: Split ladyfingers, but do not separate into individual pieces. Brush flat surfaces with creme de menthe or rum.
Line sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers, rounded sides against pan.
Separate remaining ladyfingers.
Line bottom of pan, overlapping to fit.

title: rye toast - censored zitters
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add seasonings and cheese (chopped). Spread on bread; freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in plastic bag. Before serving, brown for 5 minutes on broil.
Do not thaw before browning.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Prepare box of rice following directions on box, but leave out butter.
While rice is cooking, prepare vegetables.
Drain artichokes and save liquid.
Cut artichokes in half.

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in oleo.
Mix cheese and milk well.
Add this to vegetables, macaroni and ham; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: helen's fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Flour diced fruit with 1 cup plain flour.
Sift rest of flour together (2 cups plain, 1 cup self-rising).
Add gradually to batter; add fruit, nuts, vanilla and water.
Bake 3 1/2 hours at 225°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Do not drain tomatoes or beans.
In Dutch oven, brown meat and onion; add tomatoes and Swiss chard; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add broth, beans, water, macaroni (dry), Italian seasoning and salt.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except shrimp.
Mixer can be used. Add shrimp.
Chill and serve with long saltine crackers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine and oats.
Let stand 20 minutes, covered.
Add sugars and eggs.
Beat.
Sift together the salt, soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and flour.
Add to creamed mixture. Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost in pan with Oatmeal Cake Topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook rice and cool.
Slice broccoli and onions into food processor and process.
Mix all ingredients.
Cover and chill. Best made day before.
Serves well with grilled chicken breast, butter beans, okra and sliced tomatoes.
Enjoy!

title: company casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add two tablespoons margarine and season (salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste).
Add spaghetti and tomato sauce and simmer 1/2 hour.
In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and chopped green onion; mix well.
Cook noodles and add two tablespoons margarine.
In a 4-quart casserole baking dish, layer sauce, 1/2 noodles and spread 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layer and top with remaining sauce. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat berries in pan on stove.
Sweeten with about 1/2 cup sugar to quart of fruit.
Melt butter.
Make batter of last 4 ingredients.
Pour batter over butter, then spoon berries on top of batter.
Bake at 370° for 25 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 rolls
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise.
Add milk a little at a time.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into buttered muffin pan. Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes 12 large rolls.

title: raggedy top bars
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and brown sugar thoroughly. Add egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Blend in flour, salt and baking soda well.

title: old fashioned popcorn balls
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Continue cooking stirring constantly to hard ball stage (255°) until small amount forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat. Quickly add margarine and stir.
Slowly pour popcorn in large bowl and mix well.
Form into balls with butter hands.
Makes 15.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into cookie crust.
Refrigerate for several hours or freeze.
Garnish with peanuts if desired.

title: purple cow parfaits
directions: Blend together 2 containers yogurt, vanilla and 6 tablespoons sugar in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, blend together remaining yogurt, 3 tablespoons sugar and grape juice.
Cut bananas in half crosswise; quarter each banana half lengthwise.
Stand up 4 pieces of banana in each of 4 sundae or dessert dishes. Spoon about half of the vanilla yogurt into dish. Dividing evenly, spoon about half of the grape mixture into dish.
Dividing evenly, sprinkle each dish with 1/2 tablespoon of granola.
Repeat layering until ingredients are used up.
Top with granola and cherry.

title: the actor's ham
directions: Shake brown sugar over ham.
Affix pineapple chunks with toothpicks.
Cover with syrup.
Garnish with maraschino cherries. Bake at 350° until heated through.
Time will vary according to size of ham.

title: the best peach kuchen
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mealy.
(If using food processor, use metal chopping or plastic mixing blade.
Do not overmix; add butter in pieces and process for 1 to 2 minutes until crumbly.)
Remove 1/3 flour mixture to small bowl.
Put remaining mixture over bottom and halfway up sides of 10-[inch quiche pan or 9-inch square pan, making a crust.

title: easy chicken dinner bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in one end of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix can of cream of chicken soup, egg and milk.
Prepare dressing and put in other end of pan.
Spread soup, milk and egg mixture over entire pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.
Remove; place biscuits on top.
Bake another 15 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: governor's salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer lettuce.
Mix onion, celery and green pepper.
Put on top of lettuce.
Pour boiling water over peas to thaw, but not cook.
Drain and cool.
Place on layer 2. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise; sprinkle sugar over top of salad dressing.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon.
Crumble; cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: *Omit baking powder if using self-rising flour.

title: wassail
directions: Combine ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour. Strain mixture, discarding spices.

title: meringue that won't weep
directions: Mix cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water and cook until clear; set aside.
Beat egg whites with the salt until it stands in peaks.
Add syrup mixture.
Beat until stiff and creamy, adding 6 tablespoons sugar as you beat.
Pile on pie.
Bake 30 minutes at 325° until golden brown.
Will stand up 3 days.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute chopped onion and pepper in butter for 3 minutes.
Add meat and brown, breaking meat up.
Drain off fat. Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, pudding and milk.
Save 1/4 of chocolate bar for topping; mix in the remaining part.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for one hour.
After cake has cooled, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and chocolate bar.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Squash should be cooked about 15 minutes.
Mash squash into a pulp (some chunks are okay).
Combine with eggs and butter.
Stir well. Set aside. Combine rest of the ingredients.
Add to squash mixture.
Grease muffin tins and fill 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until picks come out clean.

title: "mammie's" one egg pudding
directions: Mix egg, sugar and butter.
Add milk, baking powder, vanilla, salt and flour.
Blend 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans or 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature. Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Bake in a 325° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until done.
Let cool before serving.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Add milk.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool in pan. Makes 16 squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix together flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Stir in bananas and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: dried beef cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: walnut delectables
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Gradually stir in flour and walnuts.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Shape into marble sized balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes until firm but not brown.
Roll gently in powdered sugar.
Cool and sugar again.
Makes 50 delicately rich cookies.

title: fudge cake("mississippi mud")
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and salt; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs one at a time. Mix cocoa with flour and add to egg mixture; mix thoroughly. Stir in chopped nuts. Pour into well greased and floured 9x13 inch cake pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees. (This will not look done.) Remove from oven and cover hot cake with the marshmallows. Put back in oven momentarily until melted; cool thoroughly. Frost.

title: tacos(filling)
directions: Brown cubed pork slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Brown taco shells.
Add filling, lettuce, chopped tomatoes and taco cheese.

title: methodist cake with a baptist touch
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Pat in bottom of 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.
Mix the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add 1 cup prepared whipped topping and spread on cooled crust.
Blend pudding mixes. Add milk and beat until thick.
Spread on cheese mixture and top with 1 cup whipped topping.
Grate chocolate bar on top and serve in squares.

title: baked carrots supreme
directions: Scrape or peel carrots.
Leave whole and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until just tender.
Cool.
Slice diagonally.
In greased casserole dish, layer carrots, brown sugar, onion flakes and crumbled bacon which has been drained.
Dot each layer with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: simple all in one cake
directions: For variety, add nuts and raisins.
Put all into a mixing bowl.
Beat 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.
Also chocolate bits can be added.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
In a large bowl, combine peas, tuna, soup, salt, pepper, cheese and cooked noodles.
Place mixture into casserole dish.

title: beef soup
directions: Boil beef bones.
When meat is almost done, add tomato soup, beef bouillon cube, celery, whole onion, green pepper, parsley carrots, bay leaf and some whole tomatoes.
Let simmer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend the two cheeses and add seasonings.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: In blender, process onion, peppers and garlic with 1/2 cup water until finely chopped.
Scrape into a saucepan; add vinegar, sugar, salt, oregano and cloves and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Cook potatoes in enough water to have 2 cups of potato water. Put water aside to cool.
Mix yeast, salt and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Cream potatoes while hot with Crisco.
Add potatoes, potato water with yeast, salt and sugar.
Let sit for 2 hours. Then work in flour.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Grate outsides of all 5 lemons.
Squeeze juice from all the lemons.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two pie shells (unbaked).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes back clean.

title: old fashioned sweet bread
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Add shortening, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend ingredients and then beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diver dan's "trauma" chili
directions: Rinse the kidney beans.
In a large pot, start simmering the sauce of canned tomatoes.
Add kidney beans and Tabasco to the simmering sauce.
Dice the peppers and onions and pan fry in a little oil until just tender.
Add	the peppers and onions to the sauce.
Brown the ground chuck in the pan.	Drain off as much of the fat as you can and add the ground chuck to the simmering pot of sauce.
Simmer the whole mixture for a least 30 minutes after adding and mixing in the chili powder.
Top with shredded cheddar cheese and a scoop of sour cream.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add rest, stirring carefully. Mix by hand (not mixer) and stir just enough to blend.
Grease and flour 4 small loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 30 minutes and remove carefully.
Wrap tightly to store thoroughly cooled. May be frozen.

title: pecan pumpkin muffins
directions: In a bowl, beat butter and sugar together until creamy and smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix until combined.
Stir in pumpkin, vanilla, lemon juice and raisins.
Pour into buttered tin and bake in preheated 325° oven until tester comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from tin and cool on wire rack.

title: marinated turkey breast
directions: Marinate turkey breasts in marinade sauce for 18 hours. Barbecue or place breasts only (no sauce) in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: butterfingers
directions: Mix corn flakes, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Form into fingers.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Melt chocolate and dip.
Let cool on plastic wrap.
Enjoy.

title: bailey's chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add alternately evaporated milk and confectioners sugar.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until thick.
Serve hot.

title: barley casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a casserole with one can of chicken broth.
Cover and bake for one hour.
Top with almonds.
Double recipe for large group.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan and pour off grease except for one tablespoon.
Saute pepper and onion in bacon grease.
Cut cabbage in small chunks; add to pepper and onion.
Saute about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add crumbled bacon, cheese and mushroom soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Spread buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes, until bubbly and bread crumbs are browned.

title: prayer meeting punch
directions: To the tea, add the frozen juices, then stir in the orange juice.
Chill and let sit until your throats are dry.

title: slow-cooked stuffed peppers
directions: Combine beef, rice mix (reserving seasoning packet), onion and egg in a large bowl.
Divide the meat mixture evenly among the pepper halves.
Pour tomatoes, with juice, into a slow cooker. Arrange filled pepper halves on top of tomatoes.
Combine tomato soup, water and rice seasoning packet in a separate bowl.
Mix well and pour over peppers.
Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pastry, and let stand for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare pastry for 9-inch pie.
Put mixture into pie crust.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Put on top crust.
Put aluminum foil around edge.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: chewy pecan cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet to cool on wire racks.
Yield:
5 to 6 dozen.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
When done, remove from pan and cool.
Cut in half to make 2 layers.
Mix the last 2 ingredients well and put half on first layer.
Put rest on top layer.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar and salt.
Microwave 8 minutes on High, stirring well after 4 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla and microwave on High 3 minutes longer.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour into lightly greased baking sheet; spread out very thin.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: goldenrod green beans
directions: Chop egg whites and press yolks through sieve.
Heat beans in their own liquid.
Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly add milk.
Stir constantly and cook until thick. Add egg whites.
Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise.
Drain beans and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with egg yolks.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and form balls the size of walnuts.
With fork, dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in cool place in candy cups or tiny baking papers.

title: ham with pineapple sauce
directions: In a skillet coated with non-stick cooking spray, heat ham slice until warmed.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients; simmer for 3 minutes.
Serve over ham. Serves 4.

title: chicken crescents
directions: In a medium bowl mix chicken, cream cheese, soup, milk and spices.
Separate crescent rolls so you have four squares.
Press very flat; spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into half of square. Fold other half at perforation and seal by pinching edges together.
Brush with melted butter and place on a cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: country cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well. Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl and add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened well.
Pour into greased dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for about 35 minutes or 20 minutes for muffins.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat the eggs, milk and butter or margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat only enough to mix.
There may be some lumps, but don't overmix.
These can be made ahead of time or the night before and refrigerate.
If refrigerated, add 1 teaspoon more baking powder to a little milk to dissolve and add to batter.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl: sugar and flour (sift twice).
Mix in saucepan:
water, butter, oil and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute.
Mix with flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and salt. Pour in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: diet oven fries
directions: Mix potatoes with olive oil.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Place on nonstick baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in the warm water for at least 5 minutes or more. To boiling water, add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast softened in water.
Gradually add 4 to 5 cups of flour.
Knead; let rise until double in bulk.
Make into cloverleaf rolls (makes 14 to 16) in greased cupcake pans.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake at 425° until brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients but cereal.
Toast Rice Krispies cereal until light brown.
Mix with the rest; roll and place in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Pinch in small balls and place on ungreased pan.
Press out with a fork.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(May lower amount of salt, if desired.)

title: easy spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix yeast, sugar, oil, egg and flour.
Place in tightly covered bowl and refrigerate.
Spoon into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Never stir down the remaining batter and be sure to keep covered.
Will keep in refrigerator for 5 to 7 days.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with the sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Combine brown sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheesy bacon nibbles
directions: Spread approximately 1 teaspoon of peanut butter on each side of cracker.
Wrap 1/2 bacon slice around cracker; use a toothpick to secure.
Place in glass dish on 4 to 5 layers of paper towels. Microwave on Medium to crisp bacon.
Top with cheese.
Microwave to melt cheese.

title: chicken and slide-downs
directions: Boil chicken pieces with vegetables in broth and water.
Do not overcook.
Strain when done and put vegetables in blender and add to stock for thickener.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Mix flour, shortening, baking powder, water and salt.
Cut as would for pie dough.
Pat out on floured surface and cut in 2-inch squares about 1/4 to 3/8-inch thick.
Let dry out 2 to 3 hours. Drop in simmering broth.
Cook on low 15 minutes, covered, and do not peek.
Add chicken; heat through and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk. Pour mixture over melted butter.
Add peaches.
Cook at 350° until crust comes to the top and browns.

title: perfect pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until moistened.
Fry in a large skillet with oil until edges are bubbly. Turn and cook until done.

title: vinegar pie shells
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg.
Add the water and vinegar to beaten egg. Mix the egg mixture with the flour and shortening.
Mix well. Form into ball and refrigerate for about 15 minutes.
Divide dough and roll between plastic wrap.
This is enough pastry for 2 single crust, 9-inch deep dish pies or at least 4 single crust 8-inch pies.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together and cool in refrigerator.

title: pepper cookies
directions: Boil raisins in 3 cups water for 3 minutes.
Pour water over shortening.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Roll like small meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk lightly.
Mix in flour, sugar, and cocoa slowly.
Cook on stove top until thickens; add margarine and vanilla.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat. In bowl, mix eggs, sugar and nuts. Pour chocolate into bowl mixture and stir until mixed well. Pour into 2 pie shells. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add enough water to crushed pineapple to make a pint (or 2 cups).
Pour this into medium size sauce pan, add 3/4 cup of sugar and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add 1 small package of lemon jello, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Set aside, when it begins to get firm - stir in 1 cup of grated American cheese. Fold in 1 cup of cool whip and nuts.
Pour into mold (4 cup size) that has been sprayed with Pam and wiped with paper towel.
Chill in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Very good served on lettuce.

title: chinese coleslaw
directions: Saute almonds and sesame seed in a little butter.
Add to coleslaw and onions.

title: no cook christmas cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows together; pour over all ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Press into desired shape. Chill 12 hours before serving.

title: * fruit cocktail cake *
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, fruit cocktail (including juice) and vanilla.
Mix together and spread in 9 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle over top with dark brown sugar, mixed with nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: large fruit salad
directions: Cook the ingredients together until thickened.
Pour the hot dressing over the prepared fruits.

title: pao doce(portuguese sweet bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in a small amount of warm milk.
Mix them with mashed potatoes.
Combine the potato mixture with the other ingredients. Cover the pan with a heavy cloth and set in a warm place to rise until doubled in bulk.
Pinch the dough off in sections, shape and put into either round or loaf pan.
Before baking, brush the loaves with egg whites or milk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: lazy rice pudding
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add rice, salt and a dab of water. Stir while boiling, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Cover and let stand and cool in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, margarine and nuts.
Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: 10 minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Store any leftover pie in the freezer.

title: glazed nuts
directions: In a heavy 8-inch skillet combine nuts, sugar and butter or margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 6 to 8 minutes or until sugar is melted and golden in color and nuts are toasted.
Spread nuts on a buttered baking sheet or aluminum foil. Separate into clusters.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cool. Makes about 1/2 pound.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and powdered sugar; add vanilla. Add Cool Whip.
Spread over graham cracker crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 3 teaspoons baking powder; stir, then add remaining 3 teaspoons baking powder and stir.
Fold in raisins. Add milk.
Bake in a cast-iron pan.
Butter pan and flour good first.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: macaroni and "cheese"
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients in blender.
Saute onion in oil. Prepare 2 cups of macaroni; cook and drain.
Mix macaroni and onion and place in dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, add extracts and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Slowly add dry ingredients into butter mixture.
Chill.
Roll out and press cookie shape. Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar; blend in flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Cut into small pieces.
Roll into ropes and twist into desired shape. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush pretzel with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake immediately at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(For hard pretzels, use only 1 1/4 cup water and add 1/4 cup melted butter.
Shape smaller and bake until brown.)

title: banana butterscotch parfaits
directions: Using 1/2 cup custard for each parfait, alternate layers of custard, sliced bananas and coconut in each of 5 parfait glasses. Repeat layers once.
Top with sliced bananas, coconut and cherries.

title: cheese bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat water and milk until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in 2 cups of the whipped topping.
Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes in a 3 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Drizzle with 1/3 of the chocolate syrup. Layer with 1/2 of the chopped candy bars and 1/2 of the pudding mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with additional chopped candy bars, if desired. Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional).
Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, chocolate, buttermilk and vanilla. Stir in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Cover and chill for 1 hour. Heat oven to 400°.

title: maple cookies(from canada)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Beat butter with sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in syrup and vanilla.
Gradually add dry ingredients, beating just until blended.
Wrap dough and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown onions in butter in same pot you are cooking soup. After onions are golden brown, add water, salt and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add milk and bring to boil.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a greased 2-quart baking dish, layer one-third of the potatoes.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one-third over the potatoes. Top with one-third of the onions. Combine soup and milk.
Pour one-third over onions.
Repeat layers twice. Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350°
for
hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: carolina barbecue
directions: Randomly pierce the surface of the roast with a sharp knife. In a Dutch oven, brown roast on all sides in hot oil.
Meanwhile,m in a bowl, combine water, tomato sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire, sugar, salt, pepper, celery seeds, chili powder, and hot pepper sauce.
Pour sauce over roast and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours or until pork is fork tender.
Baste roast with sauce during cooking time.
Slice or chop to serve.

title: easy pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in bowl of your choice. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Over low heat, cook soup, cheese, mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until cheese melts.
Add onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Cook broccoli until moisture is gone.
Place in greased casserole and pour sauce over broccoli.
Mix bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter, melted, and sprinkle over sauce.
Then sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cook chicken until changes color.
Drain off grease.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar,
add
eggs, one at a time; beat well. Use part of flour to coat candy, nuts and coconut.
Add dry ingredients alternately
with
milk.
Add
orange rind and coated candy, nuts and
coconut.
Mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan or 3 x 6-inch loaf pan in 275° oven for approximately 2 hours or until done.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain very well.
Mash squash; add other ingredients except meal.
Add more bread crumbs if necessary for easy handling.
Form into oblong croquettes and roll in meal.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish. Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir well. Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry-currant muffins
directions: Lightly coat 12 muffin tin cups with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.
Sift together cardamon, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in currants, cereal and cranberries.
In a separate bowl, whisk together buttermilk, oil, egg and maple syrup.
Gently combine contents of two bowls, stirring just until combined.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: turkey-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, peas, pimiento, salt, pepper and turkey.
Pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and sugar in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice, lemon peel and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of graham cracker crust, then add a layer of strawberries on top.
Mix 2 cups milk with pudding mixes with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand for 1 minute or until thickened.
Gently fold 1 cup whipped topping mix and add on top of strawberries.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin mixture.
Then add cream cheese and, when that is melted, add all other ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Mold and chill.
Makes approximately 4 cups.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: oatmeal brown sugar pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and oil; mixing well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add to egg mixture, mixing until blended. Stir oats into batter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: carrot coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth. Stir in pineapple, carrots and coconut.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 12 to 15.

title: fish a la delight(for the true fish lover)
directions: Put fish into pressure cooker; cook entire portion(s) until mushy and soft, including bones (tuna fish or potted meat mixture).
While fish is still hot, add cut onions, bell pepper, flour and crumbled crackers.
Make patties.
Put patties in deep fry grease; cook to desired taste.

title: spiced tea
directions: Tie cloves and cinnamon in bag.
Boil 3 minutes in water.
Tie tea in a bag and steep 3 minutes in the water.
Take out tea and spice bags.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or iced.

title: microwaved banana yummies
directions: Slice bananas.
Put 1/2 teaspoon corn oil margarine in bottom of microwave dish.
Place bananas on top of margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of bananas.
Cover and place in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Yield:
2 servings Banana Yummies.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine and simmer for about 1 hour.
Stir frequently.

title: bacon and tomato - potato shells
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cool; then slice lengthwise and scoop out the center of each half.
Leave about 1/4-inch thick shell.
Save the centers for mashed potatoes later.
Combine the oil, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Brush inside of each shell with the mixture.
Place on a baking sheet and fill each shell with bacon, tomato and green onion.
Top with cheese and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted and shells are heated through.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Shells can be covered and refrigerated for 24 hours before baking for make-ahead ease.

title: creme puff cake(really good, light and yummy)
directions: Heat water and oleo to boiling.
Add flour, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°. Cool completely.

title: chicken quesadillas ole
directions: Saute peppers, onions and mushrooms in butter until tender. Place some pepper mixture on flour shell.
Sprinkle with cheese. Fold in half; secure with toothpick.
Place in a hot buttered skillet; heat until golden brown on both sides.
Serve hot with sour cream and salsa.
This recipe is great with leftovers or can increase to feed many.

title: mom's bean and spaghetti dinner
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook in a little fat. Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes.
Add spaghetti, baked beans and corn.
Heat and serve.

title: oil and vinegar grilled chicken
directions: Mix together and pour over 1 cut up fryer.
Marinate at least 1 hour or longer if you wish, then cook on hot grill until done.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. This makes two 9-inch pies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: simply beef
directions: In medium saucepan, place all ingredients with just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; immediately reduce to simmer. Continue to cook until all redness is gone, using a fork to separate meat.
Drain.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth in consistency. Serve with fresh fruit.
Delicious with sliced apples and strawberries.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Drain the fat, then add all other ingredients. Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: spiced cider
directions: Heat slowly.
Add more brown sugar or honey to taste.
Strain into cups.

title: easiest dinner ever
directions: Brown 4 to 6 (or number needed) pork chops.
Drain.
Place back in pan and cover with a jar of salsa.
Cook over low heat 30 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy with rice, noodles or tortillas.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add cooked onion.
Blend together the soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix beans with meat after meat is cooked.
Crush Doritos chips and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer meat and onion mixture over the chips. Pour the blended soups and tomatoes over this.
Add grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is hot.

title: water whip pie shell
directions: Mix Crisco, water and milk until blended to a milky consistency. Add flour and salt.
Mix.
Roll into pie crusts. Makes 2 crusts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add soups and water.
Stir well to combine.
Bring to a boil.
Measure rice into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour about 2/3 of the soup mixture over rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Cover and bake in a 275° oven for 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8. "Can be cooking while I'm at church."

title: baked lasagna
directions: Saute meat (ground beef and ground sausage) in olive oil, breaking it into small bits as it browns.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt and oregano.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Have ready bottom pie shell.
