Coat pie shell generously with egg white.

title: david's brilliant cookies
directions: *Measure flour and powdered sugar after sifting.

title: (make ahead) joes to go
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Add garlic salt, pepper, chili sauce, brown sugar, white vinegar, mustard and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and freeze.

title: hummingbird feed
directions: Boil water and sugar 2 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add red food coloring.
Let cool.
Fill feeder.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until it stands in peaks. Add the sugar gradually, beating continuously.
Flavor with vanilla.
Spread meringue onto a heavily oiled brown paper-lined cookies sheet or force meringue through a cake decorator or cookie tube.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Loosen paper lining.
While hot, spread the filling.
Roll as for jelly roll.

title: hobo dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and eat with chips as a dip.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pineapple with its juice.
Lightly beat eggs and add.
Mix well.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in a 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add eggs; beat well. Add applesauce and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake for about 2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: The mashed vanilla bean may be added to the sugar and stored in an airtight container so the sugar absorbs the flavor of the vanilla, this may be done well in advance.

title: haddock-shrimp bake
directions: Place shrimp and haddock in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread soup over top.
Add crushed crackers with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: orange egg nog
directions: Whip eggs in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Add the sugar and spices and whip again.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with a little nutmeg and lots of cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: pizza pan breakfast
directions: Press pizza crust on pizza pan forming the crust.
Brown and drain sausage.
Crumble and sprinkle over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns and cheese over meat.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together. Pour mixture over pizza. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, eggs, salt and pepper to taste and onion together. Add enough cornmeal to make mixture stiff enough to shape into croquettes.
Fry in hot skillet with deep Crisco oil.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Cut cherries in half.
Cool two hours.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruit.
Add coconut and whipped topping.
Stir the ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: oreo cookie ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into an aluminum-foil lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours or until firm. This mixture may also be frozen in a regular ice cream freezer.

title: boffo bread
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Saute chopped garlic and onion until brown; add chopped tomatoes and olives.
Cook for about 5 minutes, then add basil and oregano and cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut bread in half lengthwise and then into half again; scoop out bread, making a trough (give scooped bread to local ducks or geese); divide sauteed ingredients and spoon into trough.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp.
Add shredded cheese and place under broiler for 30 to 60 seconds or until cheese melts. Serve as soon as possible.
To serve, cut into smaller pieces.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cut potatoes in cubes. Sprinkle Italian dressing over potatoes. Separate onion slices and place over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: corn custard casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and salt in the butter.
Combine both cans of corn, eggs, muffin mix and 1 cup cheese.
Mix with onion mixture and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: braised red cabbage and apples
directions: Melt bacon grease in a large skillet; add sugar and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add onions and cook slowly until lightly colored.
Stir in cabbage, apples, vinegar, wine and spices.
Cook over low heat, covered, for 10 minutes, then add water and cook, with cover askew, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 40 minutes. Add salt to taste.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Saute and drain sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Layer bread, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Arrange the potatoes in an 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine the butter and garlic in a small microwave safe dish. Microwave on HIGH for 30 seconds or until butter melts; stir. Drizzle the butter mixture over the potatoes. Sprinkle with the green onions and grated cheese. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until the potatoes are tender and light brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins(yield:  8 - 10 muffins)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: golden lemonade
directions: Combine fruit juices and water; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 36.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl. Cut in butter and shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle in the lemon juice or vinegar and 5 to 6 tablespoons cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, and toss until dough just comes together in clumps. Shape into 2 discs, one slightly larger than the other. Wrap in plastic and refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Makes 1 (2 crust) 9-inch pie.

title: pizza hot dish(a two-crust pizza pie)
directions: Lay flat:
one package of crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add the Sloppy Joe mix, tomato sauce and oregano.
Mix well and pour over the dough. Sprinkle cheese over the top and place the second package of crescent roll dough over the top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° or until brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Place popcorn in roasting pan.
In medium pan on stove heat brown sugar, margarine, white corn syrup and salt to bubbling boil.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Stir in soda then mix into popcorn and place in oven for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip; add lemonade.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: easy carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. Serves 4.

title: jack's new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and reserve juice. Cook bacon until crispy, crumble and put aside. Saute diced onion, add crumbled bacon, potatoes and clam juice and simmer until potatoes are tender. Stir flour into half and half and slowly add this into the pot. Stir until thicker. Add salt, pepper and clams. Turn off burner. Add butter and stir.

title: canadian war cake(3 layers)
directions: Note:
This cake does not call for eggs.

title: five minute noodle stew
directions: Boil 4 cups water with bouillon cubes.
Add noodles.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in seasoning
from flavor packets.
Add stewed tomatoes (and mushrooms).
Heat until hot.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Wash blueberries and dry on paper towels.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend in sifted flour, sifted with baking powder.
Fold in the berries gently.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch metal pan at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into squares and serve from the pan.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 16 squares.

title: raspberry ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in raspberries, pineapple and chopped pecans.
Blend well.

title: pepperoni and cheese loaf
directions: Thaw dough and allow to rise according to package directions. Divide dough in half and set one portion aside.
Turn out one portion of dough on a lightly floured surface.
Roll dough into a 10-inch circle.

title: microwave pickled frank kabobs
directions: Cut each frank in 8 pieces.
Arrange kabob-style on toothpicks.
Start with frank, then pickle, etc.
Shake 2 or 3 drops of liquid smoke on each kabob.
Arrange kabobs in a circle on plate.
Microwave 1/2 minute on High for 6 kabobs.
Makes 32.

title: angel food pudding cake
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bottom of cake pan.
Prepare the vanilla pudding with skim milk and spread over cake.
Sprinkle strawberries or cherries over the pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and mustard.
Cook rotini; drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients.
Toss with dressing.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crazy crust apple pie(try it and see)
directions: Combine filling with juice and spice and pour into center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: melt in mouth
directions: After eggs whites are stiff, mix in other ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish and bake at 425° for about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crock-pot meatballs in gravy
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except gravy.
Shape into meatballs and brown in skillet or on broiler rack in a 400° oven. Prepare gravy in crock-pot.
Add meatballs.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours (on high setting for 3 to 4 hours). Makes 4 to 6 servings (about 2 quarts).

title: icebox cake
directions: Whip cream.
Add enough syrup to taste chocolatey.
Place a row of graham crackers in bottom of a square dish or pan.
Spread on some chocolate cream.
Keep alternating until dish is full. End with cream.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut and enjoy.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Bring to a boil potatoes, celery, onion, carrots and green pepper.
Boil 15 minutes or until desired tenderness.
Turn down on low; simmer.
Add corn, peas, corned beef, Veg-All, green beans, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with saltine crackers on a cool day.

title: peaches 'n cream cheese pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding, butter, egg and milk; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Place peaches over batter.

title: roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, salsa, onions and olives.
Spread thinly on tortillas.
Arrange slices of corned beef on cheese.
Roll up tightly.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 3 hours.
To serve, cut into 3/4-inch slices.

title: yum yum cake(weight watchers)
directions: Slice angel food cake; cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple with juice over cake.
Mix pudding according to directions; pour over pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with shredded coconut, if desired.
You can also put sliced bananas over cake before adding pineapple.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Sift first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and water.
Mix all together well.
Pour into greased coffee cans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done; drain and mash.
Add onions and egg. Cook in pan like dressing with liquid mix and chicken bouillon cube.
Add seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or an hour.

title: outrageously simple beef stew
directions: In a stew pot with top, simmer all ingredients except for vegetables for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook another 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and
egg;
pat evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sugar, cream
cheese,
vanilla
and eggs;
pour over cake mix mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, 6 cups sugar and allspice.
Pour over pickles.
Next day, add 2 cups sugar.
Each day add 2 cups sugar. On the third day, can.
Put a couple of allspice in each jar.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Stir until melted.
Add milk and boil 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir until smooth.

title: carrot-raisin brownies
directions: Mix flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream butter. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add raisins and carrots.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with Italian dressing. Roll chicken until covered.
Leave remaining dressing in dish. Sprinkle lemon pepper over chicken until completely covered.
Bake at 350° until brown, turning once every 30 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, but bananas and chill.
Add sliced bananas before serving.

title: pecan - chicken log
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Blend in next 2 ingredients. Shape into a 9-inch log or 2 (4 1/2-inch) logs. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 4 hours or overnight. Combine chopped parsley and pecan pieces. Roll logs in this mixture and coat thoroughly. Serve with crackers. Makes 3 cups spread.

title: individual baked alaska
directions: Combine egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt in a mixer bowl.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly until stiff peaks form.
Place sponge cakes on a foil-lined wooden cutting board.
Place 1 ice cream patty in each cup.
Cover each with meringue, sealing meringue to bottom of sponge cups.
Sprinkle with crushed peppermint candy.
Bake at 500° for 2 to 3 minutes or until light brown.
Serve immediately. Serves 2.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Dip cutlets into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Brown on both sides.
Arrange cutlets in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour Tomato Sauce over cutlets (recipe follows).

title: chocolate cornflake confections
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate pieces.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and extract until smooth and blended.
Stir in cornflakes and coconut until well combined.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheets lined with parchment paper.
Gently press cherry piece in middle of each.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until firm to touch.
Remove immediately to racks to cool.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued hamburger mix
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ground beef; brown lightly. Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Makes 30 to 40 hamburger buns.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch long pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer until done.

title: spiced stew
directions: Brown meat in hot shortening. Add onions and enough water to nearly cover.
Mix sugar and cinnamon with lemon juice and add with bay leaves and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover, bring slowly to boiling point, then simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours.

title: applesauce raisin spice squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine raisins with baking soda and boiling water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
In a medium size bowl, combine flour, cinnamon and salt.
In a large bowl, beat together applesauce, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with raisin mixture, beginning and ending with flour. Mix by hand until flour mixture is combined with raisin mixture. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove loaf from pan. Place on wire rack to cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: granny's whipping cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
Measure and sift the flour and divide it into 3 parts.
Alternately, add one part of the flour and some whipping cream until all the ingredients are mixed well. Add the vanilla; mix well.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: dandy beef corn casserole
directions: Brown together hamburg and onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes and corn to hamburg.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 pound of Cheddar cheese cubes.
I use Velveeta.
Immediately turn heat off and cover skillet.
Cheese will melt in about a minute.

title: cowboy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Add oats and nuts and mix.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: italian mushroom grill
directions: Combine mushrooms and salad dressing in a small bowl and toss to coat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Thread mushrooms on skewers and place 6 inches above hot coals.
Grill 5 minutes or until tender, turning often and brushing with remaining salad dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake*
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Alternate milk and flour. Bake at 275° until done.

title: fried corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together with tap water until not too stiff.
Drop in skillet of oil on medium-high heat and fry slowly (about 1
or
tablespoonfuls at a time) until golden brown.

title: tasty sausage and peppers
directions: Bake sausages until brown (for approximately 30 minutes at 400°).
Remove sausages; let cool.
Dice onions.
Slice peppers and leave in a separate pan.
Cut sausage into 1-inch sections. Mix sausages, onions and peppers into a deep dish pan.
Mix in whole tomatoes.
Cover with foil.
Place into oven and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: brown bread
directions: Boil raisins in water; let cool.
Mix other ingredients; add raisins and one cup of raisin liquid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 4 (No. 2) cans.

title: cheesy dijon chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, basil and onion powder.
Spread one side of chicken breasts with mustard.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Dip into eggs, then again into crumbs.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni as package directs.
In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook 6 minutes on each side or until brown.
Top rice with chicken and cheese.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and pour over the combined vegetables, cheese and bacon bits.
Marinate overnight and serve cool.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in oil.
Add enough milk to make soft, stiff dough.
Thinly roll out dough on lightly floured board into 2 rectangles, 10 x 1-inch.
Spread sausage on each rectangle and roll up lengthwise.
Chill or freeze.
Slice in 5/8-inch slices and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken "n" cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large casserole dish, combine all ingredients, mixing well. Cover and bake for 35 to 45 minutes. Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer. Serve immediately.

title: fried vegetables
directions: According to amount of vegetables you are going to use: Beat eggs
with
salt
and
pepper.
Wash and drain vegetables until dry.
Dip
vegetables into a beaten egg, salt and pepper mixture. Mix
in
Ziploc or grocery bag:
3/4 cup cornmeal to 1/4 cup flour.
Drop
in
egg-coated
vegetables and coat the vegetables with
cornmeal/flour
mixture, then fry in cooking oil until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Smash crackers and add melted butter.
Pat into 9 x 13 dish. Mix broccoli and soup together and pour over crackers; even out and cover with American cheese slices.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add oil, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead a few times on floured surface.
Roll thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter and dip in melted margarine.
Stack in two's.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 18 to 20 biscuits.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, 3/4 cup of sugar, salt and beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch pan with graham cracker crust bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Prepare 3 packages of Dream Whip as per directions on the box. Blend in Jell-O.
Mix in drained fruit cocktail and marshmallows. Chill about 2 hours.
Serve cold.
Very refreshing!

title: colorado beans
directions: Fry bacon until done.
Drain and keep until later.
Cook sliced onions in bacon grease.
It is best to cover skillet and let them cook slowly until they are limp.
Add brown sugar and vinegar.
Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Add beans to onions along with crumbled bacon.
Bake in 2-quart casserole or bean pot at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted butter. Stir until crumbly.
Press half of the oat mixture into a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Cover with apples.
In a medium saucepan combine white sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Pour over apples. Cover apples with the remaining crumble mixture.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes, until bubbly and golden.

title: dutch oven bake
directions: In Dutch oven, bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Place 2 packages jello in saucepan with 3/4 cup liquid (use cherry juice, pineapple juice and water to make 3/4 cup liquid) and heat until jello is dissolved.
Allow to cool.
Add cherries, cheese, nuts, pineapple and Coke.
Let congeal; cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: christmas potpourri
directions: Simmer on stove in pan, uncovered, during the holidays or any time you want that holiday aroma.

title: golden stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: onkers
directions: Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add butter; mix well with fork.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around each "surprise" (olive or wiener).
Shape into ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: squash pickles
directions: Peel, seed and cut squash into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine water, sugar, vinegar, turmeric, ginger, salt and dry mustard in a large saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil; add squash and onions.
Boil 10 minutes.
Pack hot into jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps (process 10 minutes in boiling water bath).
Yields about 2 1/2 pints.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: You may heat the cherries and add 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar for taste (I never do).

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut crab delights flakes in half or shred.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Serve as a sandwich or on lettuce.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Mix all together.
Roll thin.
Put filling in and cook in deep oil.

title: rhubarb squares
directions: In a 7 x 10-inch pan, spread rhubarb in bottom, 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle the sugar over rhubarb, then sprinkle jello and cake mix.
Add the water and melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: red apple diabetic delight
directions: In a large stew pot, place apples carefully in hot to boiling water. Simmer 3 minutes. Turn over apples and simmer 3 minutes longer.

Test often with test needle or toothpick (should slide out easily). Remove apples and place on paper towels to drain. Serve warm or cool with your favorite topping such as Cool Whip, drizzled cream cheese or diabetic ice cream. Great stored in a covered container and frozen for future use.

title: 1 hour rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Add warm milk, water and oleo.
Mix 2 minutes with mixer.
Add 1/2 cup flour. Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise 15 minutes in greased bowl.
Make into dinner rolls or cinnamon rolls.
Let rise in pan for 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: basic brownie for the microwave
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, and vanilla together.
Add melted butter. Continue beating.
Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8 inch square dish.
Microwave on high for 6 minutes.
Cut when cook.
You can sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Serve with ice cream.

title: french onion soup
directions: In covered 2 1/2 quart casserole, cook onions and oleo on high for 10 minutes.
Stir in broth, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Cover.
Cook on high for 5 minutes and spoon into soup bowls suitable for microwave use.
Sprinkle toast with cheese and float on top of soup.
Microwave on high for 30 seconds.

title: quick punch
directions: Put ingredients in gallon pitcher and add water enough to make 1 gallon.

title: carrot salad
directions: Whip cream and mix in all ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.
Makes extra large amount.

title: twenty four hour cole slaw
directions: Cover cabbage and onions with sugar.
Bring vinegar, celery seed, salt and mustard to a boil, then add salad oil.
Bring to a boil again and pour over cabbage, cover and let set 24 hours.

title: old time molasses cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and pour in boiling water; beat until smooth.
Beat eggs and pour into batter.
Mix well. May add nuts, if you wish.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake 30 minutes (or until done) at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve hot with butter.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Make centers by mixing margarine, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Roll these in small balls and dip in chocolate mixture (melt chocolate and paraffin wax together).
Cool on wax paper.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together, shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix will. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash, drain and hull berries.
Leave whole.
Put in saucepan. Sprinkle 1/3 cup sugar over berries.
Pour lemon juice over top and let stand in cool place overnight (do not refrigerate). Next morning, add 2 1/2 cups sugar, heat to a boil and boil 7 minutes, counting from time boiling begins.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: company chicken breasts
directions: Wrap dried beef slices (2 each) around each chicken breast. Wrap 1 slice bacon around each beef-wrapped chicken breast and secure with toothpick.
Combine mushroom soup, sour cream and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake covered, for 2 hours 45 minutes at 250 degrees.
Uncover and brown just before serving.

title: shrimp and corn chowder
directions: Mix soup and milk in 4-quart saucepan.
Stir in potatoes. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add scallions and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in cooked shrimp.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Mix Bleu cheese and cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pasta salad
directions: Can also add shredded cheese.

title: easy-do-fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter or margarine in a large heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Stir constantly, about 5 minutes, over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°). Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: scotch cakes
directions: Add soda to butter and cream well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.	Put in cupcake pan.
Bake in a mild oven (275° to 300°) approximately 30 minutes.

title: tom selleck cake
directions: Poke holes in baked cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over evenly.
Pour topping over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip and then sprinkle crushed Heath bars over all.
Chill.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in a cold oven; set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving dish. If desired, drizzle glaze over top and sides.

title: mary's cheezy crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except crab and 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Fold in crab meat.
Put in 1 1/2 quart greased casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cranberry-nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Put orange juice and rind in measuring cup. Add shortening and then fill cup to the 3/4 mark with boiling water.
Add to dry mixture and mix.

title: cheesy tater topper
directions: In a small saucepan stir together milk, cornstarch, mustard and pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in mixed vegetables and heat through.
Serve warm over baked potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: wesson sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs real good with mixer.
Dissolve the salt, baking powder, vanilla and soda in buttermilk.
Add this to the sugar, oil and egg mixture.
Add 6 cups of all-purpose flour; mix well.
Use 1/4 cup measure, not full, and put 6 to a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Line large baking dish with tortillas.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add beans, enchilada sauce and chicken or mushroom soup.
Add green chilies.
Pour over tortillas; add grated cheese over layered tortillas.
Top with stewed tomatoes or more green chilies.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious.

title: shirley's banana bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, shortening until light and fluffy. Add bananas, flour, and blend. Add nuts. Place mixture into lightly greased loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: dill pickles
directions: Select medium size pickling cucumbers.
Wash and pack in sterilized jars.
To each quart, add 2 bunches dill, 1 piece alum (size of small grape) and 2 teaspoons mustard seed.
Fill jars with hot brine made from the vinegar, water and salt.
Seal.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake together and cool.
Unroll.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat smooth.
Spread on cake and roll up.
Chill.
Cut into slices.

title: triple treats
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening over hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour half of mixture into 8-inch foil lined pan.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until set.
Return remaining half to hot water.
Melt caramels and butter.
Add water over low heat, stirring until melted and smooth.
Stir in nuts. Blend well and pour over chocolate chips in refrigerator.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until tacky (about 15 minutes).
Top with remaining chocolate.
Spread evenly.
Return to refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Put sugar, dates and eggs in greased frying pan.
Stir constantly, 7 to 10 minutes, mashing dates as you stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir into mixture until well mixed.
Start pan on hot.
When hot, turn to low.
When all is mixed, turn out on wax paper.
On another sheet of wax paper, empty can of Angel Flake coconut.
As soon as mixture is cool enough to handle, grease hands and form balls, fingers or any other shape you might want.
Roll in coconut.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger in saucepan.
Add salt and pepper.
When fully cooked, drain off grease.
Mix in 1 cup spaghetti sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses set out to room temperature.
Cream together; add pecans, garlic salt and paprika.
Roll in additional pecans. Refrigerate overnight.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add
the
rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Put in pie plate and bake
in
a
350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Clean the lentils and rinse with cold water.
Combine the lentils and the water in a pot.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and lower the heat.
Do not cover and cook until soft for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Crush in the blender, then place back in the pot and add the salt, oil and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve with your favorite bread.

title: hot sausage cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix sausage, cheese, Tabasco, Bisquick and milk.
Make into balls; place on greased (I use Pam) cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: uncooked oatmeal fudge
directions: Mix in a large saucepan the margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa. Let boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper or tinfoil and let cool.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Soak 1 box "fish eye" tapioca in water overnight; drain. Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Cook about 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
(Make sure water doesn't boil out of pan.) Serve warm with dessert topping.

title: bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onion and salt. Spread over beans and corn.
Put crushed crackers and almonds on top.
Melt margarine.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: disappearing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, excluding water, in a large mixing bowl. Add boiling water.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: applesauce pork chops
directions: Rinse chops, then put in marinade sauce (ingredients above except chops) and leave in for 4 to 6 hours.
Shake off excess applesauce and put on the hot grill.
Great on the grill!
Cooking time varies as to thickness of the chops.
Allow 35 to 45 minutes. (Turn often because of the sugar; they brown easily.)

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in the wheat germ.
Add all remaining ingredients and beat until well-blended.
Place in an oiled 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, coconut, pineapple and melted butter; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until well set.
